  nickname: pro
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 69cda689d36a6b64ca4a020e1d829e9f, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Prologue'
      title: The Prologue
      number: 1
      content: "Here are kingdom revelations, words to live by,and words of wisdom
        given to empower you to reign in life, [[COMMENT(0)]]written as proverbs
        by Israel\u2019s King Solomon,  David\u2019s son."
      comments:
      - number: 1:1
        content: "  As stated in the introduction, the Hebrew word for \u201Cproverbs\u201D
          means more than just a wise saying. It can also mean \u201Cto rule, to
          reign in power, to take dominion.\u201D      The name Solomon means \u201Cpeaceable.\u201D
          There is a greater one than Solomon who gives peace to all of his followers.
          His name is Jesus. Solomon was the seed of David; we are the seed of Jesus
          Christ. Solomon had an encounter with God after asking for a discerning
          heart (). This pleased God, so he gave Solomon wisdom, riches, and power.
          God is ready to impart these same things today to those who ask him. See 
          .    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Within these sayings will be found the revelation of wisdom [[COMMENT(0)]]and
        the impartation of spiritual understanding.Use them as keys to unlock the
        treasures of true knowledge.
      comments:
      - number: 1:2
        content: "  There are six Hebrew words translated \u201Cwisdom\u201D in the
          book of Proverbs. Some of them require an entire phrase in English to convey
          the meaning. The word used here is  , and it is used in Proverbs forty-two
          times. Forty-two is the number of months Jesus ministered and the number
          of generations from Abraham to Christ listed in  .    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Those who cling to these words will receive disciplineto demonstrate
        wisdom [[COMMENT(0)]] in every relationshipand to choose what is right and
        just and fair.
      comments:
      - number: 1:3
        content: "  The Hebrew word translated \u201Cwisdom\u201D here also means
          \u201Crighteousness.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: These proverbs will give you great skillto teach the immature and
        make them wise,to give youth the understanding of their design and destiny.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: For the wise, these proverbs will make you even wiser,and for those
        with discernment,you will be able to acquire brilliant strategies for leadership.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: These kingdom revelations will break open your understandingto unveil
        the deeper meaning of parables,poetic riddles, and epigrams,and to unravel
        the words and enigmas of the wise.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Wisdom of a Father'
      title: The Wisdom of a Father
      number: 7
      content: We cross the threshold of true knowledgewhen we live in obedient devotion
        to God. [[COMMENT(0)]]Stubborn know-it-alls  will never stop to do this,for
        they scorn true wisdom and knowledge.
      comments:
      - number: 1:7
        content: "  Many translations render this \u201Cthe fear of the Lord.\u201D
          This means much more than the English concept of fear. It also implies
          submission, awe, worship, and reverence. The Hebrew word used here is found
          fourteen times in Proverbs. The number fourteen represents spiritual perfection.
          The number fourteen is mentioned three times in the genealogy of Jesus
          (). It is also the number for Passover. You will pass from darkness to
          wisdom\u2019s light by the \u201Cfear\u201D of the Lord.      Or \u201Cfoolish
          ones.\u201D There are three Hebrew words translated \u201Cfool\u201D in
          Proverbs and another six that are related to a fool or foolish acts. A
          fool is described in Proverbs as one who hates true wisdom and correction,
          with no desire to acquire revelation knowledge.    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Pay close attention, my child, to your father\u2019s wise wordsand
        never forget your mother\u2019s instructions. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 1:8
        content: '  Many expositors see this verse as the words of David to Solomon,
          yet we all must give heed to this command. The words of our Father (God)
          and our mother (the church, the freewoman) will bring us wisdom. See  .    '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: For their insight will bring you success,adorning you with grace-filled
        thoughtsand giving you reins to guide your decisions. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 1:9
        content: "  The Hebrew text here is literally translated \u201Cadornment
          for your head, chains for your neck.\u201D The head is a metaphor for our
          thoughts, the neck a symbol for willing obedience that guides our decisions,
          in contrast to being stiff-necked or proud. See  .    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "When peer pressure compels you to go with the crowdand sinners invite
        you to join in,you must simply say, \u201CNo!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "When the gang says\u2014\u201CWe\u2019re going to steal and kill
        and get away with it."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "We\u2019ll take down the rich and rob them.We\u2019ll swallow them
        up aliveand take what we want from whomever we want."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then we\u2019ll take their treasures and fill our homes with loot."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So come on and join us.Take your chance with us.We\u2019ll divide
        up all we get;we\u2019ll each end up with big bags of cash!\u201D\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: my son, refuse to go with them and stay far away from them.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: For crime is their way of life and bloodshed their specialty.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: To be aware of their snare is the best way of escape.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "They\u2019ll resort to murder to steal their victim\u2019s assets,but
        eventually it will be their own lives that are ambushed."
      comments: []
    - name: "19: Wisdom\u2019s Warning"
      title: "Wisdom\u2019s Warning"
      number: 19
      content: In their ungodly disrespect for Godthey bring destruction on their
        own lives.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Wisdom\u2019s praises are sung in the streetsand celebrated far and
        wide."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Yet wisdom\u2019s song is not always heard in the halls of higher
        learning.But in the hustle and bustle of everyday lifeits lyrics can always
        be heard above the din of the crowd. [[COMMENT(0)]]You will hear wisdom\u2019s
        warning as she preaches courageouslyto those who stop to listen:"
      comments:
      - number: 1:21
        content: "  Literally translated, this verse reads \u201CWisdom sings out
          in the streets and speaks her voice in the squares, crying out at the head
          of noisy crowds and at the entrance of the city gates.\u201D This is a
          parabolic statement of wisdom being heard everywhere and in every place.    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CFoolish ones, how much longer will you cling to your deception?
        [[COMMENT(0)]]How much longer will you mock wisdom,you cynical scorners who
        fight the facts?"
      comments:
      - number: 1:22
        content: "  Or \u201CChildish ones, how long will you love your childishness?\u201D    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Come back to your senses and be restored to reality.Don\u2019t even
        think about refusing my rebuke!Don\u2019t you know that I\u2019m readyto
        pour out my spirit of wisdom upon youand bring to you the revelation of my
        wordsthat will make your heart wise?"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "I\u2019ve called to you over and over;still you refuse to come to
        me.I\u2019ve pleaded with you again and again,yet you\u2019ve turned a deaf
        ear to my voice."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Because you have laughed at my counseland have insisted on continuing
        in your stubbornness,
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "I will laugh when your calamity comesand will turn away from you
        at the time of your disaster.Make a joke of my advice, will you?Then I\u2019ll
        make a joke out of you!"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: When the storm clouds of terror gather over your head,when dread and
        distress consume youand your catastrophe comes like a hurricane,
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "you will cry out to me, but I won\u2019t answer.Then it will be too
        late to expect my help.When desperation drives you to search for me,I will
        be nowhere to be found."
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Because you have turned up your nose at meand closed your eyes to
        the factsand refused to worship me in awe [[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014"
      comments:
      - number: 1:29
        content: "  The Hebrew word used here can be translated \u201Cfear,\u201D
          \u201Cdread,\u201D \u201Cawe,\u201D or \u201Cworship.\u201D Nearly every
          translation uses the word    or    while ignoring the other aspects of
          the Aramaic word  . The New Testament is clear that there is no fear in
          love. See  .    "
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "because you scoffed at my wise counseland laughed at my correction\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "now you will eat the bitter fruit of your own ways.You\u2019ve made
        your own bed; now lie in it!So how do you like that?"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Like an idiot you\u2019ve turned away from meand chosen destruction
        instead.Your self-satisfied smugness [[COMMENT(0)]] will kill you."
      comments:
      - number: 1:32
        content: "  Or \u201Cyour abundant prosperity.\u201D  "
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "But the one who always listens to mewill live undisturbed in a heavenly
        peace.Free from fear, confident and courageous,that one will rest unafraid
        and sheltered from the storms of life.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Searching for Wisdom'
      title: Searching for Wisdom
      number: 1
      content: My child, will you treasure my wisdom?Then, and only then, will you
        acquire it.And only if you accept my adviceand hide it within will you succeed.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So train your heart to listen when I speakand open your spirit wide
        to expand your discernment\u2014then pass it on to your sons and daughters.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 2:2
        content: '  As translated from the Septuagint.    '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Yes, cry out for comprehension and intercede for insight.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: For if you keep seeking it like a man would seek for sterling silver,searching
        in hidden places for cherished treasure,
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: then you will discover the fear of the Lordand find the true knowledge
        of God.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Wisdom is a gift from a generous God,and every word he speaks is full
        of revelationand becomes a fountain of understanding within you. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 2:6
        content: "  The Septuagint adds \u201Cfound in his presence.\u201D    "
    - name: '7-8: '
      title: 
      number: 7-8
      content: For the Lord has a hidden storehouse of wisdommade accessible to his
        godly ones. [[COMMENT(0)]]He becomes your personal bodyguard as you follow
        his ways,protecting and guarding you as you choose what is right.
      comments:
      - number: "2:7\u20138"
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe righteous.\u201D    "
    - name: '7-8: '
      title: 
      number: 7-8
      content: For the Lord has a hidden storehouse of wisdommade accessible to his
        godly ones. [[COMMENT(0)]]He becomes your personal bodyguard as you follow
        his ways,protecting and guarding you as you choose what is right.
      comments:
      - number: "2:7\u20138"
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe righteous.\u201D    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Then you will discover all that is just, proper, and fair,and be empowered
        to make the right decisionsas you walk into your destiny.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: When wisdom wins your heart and revelation breaks in,true pleasure
        enters your soul.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: If you choose to follow good counsel,divine design will watch over
        youand understanding will protect youfrom making poor choices.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: It will rescue you from evil in disguiseand from those who speak duplicities.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: For they have left the paths of righteousnessand walk in the ways
        of darkness.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: They take pleasure when evil prospersand thoroughly enjoy a lifestyle
        of sin.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Wisdom, the Way of the Pure'
      title: Wisdom, the Way of the Pure
      number: 15
      content: "But they\u2019re walking on a path to nowhere,wandering away into
        deeper deception."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Only wisdom can save you from the flatteryof the promiscuous woman\u2014she\u2019s
        such a smooth-talking seductress!"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: She left her husband and has forgotten her wedding vows. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 2:17
        content: "  Clearly this is a warning to those who would commit adultery,
          but there is a deeper meaning within this text. Proverbs tells us of two
          women: the adulteress and the virtuous woman of  . Both women speak a parable
          of two systems in the church. One is religious and alluring, tempting the
          young anointed ones to come to her \u201Cbed\u201D of compromise (see 
          ). The other is the holy bride, virtuous and pure, keeping her first love
          (\u201Cwedding vows\u201D) for Christ alone. Her \u201Chouse\u201D is the
          house of the Lord (see  ). One system brings shame and despair; the other
          brings favor, honor, and glory. It is wisdom that protects us from one
          and unites us to the other. See    and  .    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "You\u2019ll find her house on the road to hell,"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and all the men who go through her doorswill never come back to the
        place they were\u2014they will find nothing but desolation and despair."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Follow those who follow wisdom and stay on the right path.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: For all my godly lovers will enjoy life to the fullestand will inherit
        their destinies. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 2:21
        content: "  Literally \u201Cshall dwell in the land.\u201D  "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: But the treacherous ones who love darknesswill lose not only all they
        could have had,but even their own souls!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1-2: The Rewards of Wisdom'
      title: The Rewards of Wisdom
      number: 1-2
      content: "My child, if you truly want a long and satisfying life,never forget
        the things that I\u2019ve taught you.Follow closely every truth that I\u2019ve
        given you.Then you will have a full, rewarding life."
      comments: []
    - name: '1-2: The Rewards of Wisdom'
      title: The Rewards of Wisdom
      number: 1-2
      content: "My child, if you truly want a long and satisfying life,never forget
        the things that I\u2019ve taught you.Follow closely every truth that I\u2019ve
        given you.Then you will have a full, rewarding life."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Hold on to loyal love and don\u2019t let go,and be faithful to all
        that you\u2019ve been taught.Let your life be shaped by integrity, [[COMMENT(0)]]with
        truth written upon your heart."
      comments:
      - number: 3:3
        content: "  Or \u201CTie my commands around your neck.\u201D The neck is
          a symbol of our will and conscience.    "
    - name: "4: Wisdom\u2019s Guidance"
      title: "Wisdom\u2019s Guidance"
      number: 4
      content: "That\u2019s how you will find favor and understandingwith both God
        and men\u2014you will gain the reputation of living life well."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Trust in the Lord completely,and do not rely on your own opinions.With
        all your heart rely on him to guide you,and he will lead you in every decision
        you make.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Become intimate with him in whatever you do,and he will lead you wherever
        you go. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 3:6
        content: "  Or \u201Che will cut a straight path before you.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Don\u2019t think for a moment that you know it all, [[COMMENT(0)]]for
        wisdom comes when you adore him with undivided devotionand avoid everything
        that\u2019s wrong."
      comments:
      - number: 3:7
        content: '  We should always be willing to listen to correction and instruction.    '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Then you will find the healing refreshmentyour body and spirit long
        for. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 3:8
        content: "  Literally \u201Chealing to your navel and moistening to your
          bones.\u201D The blood supply for a baby in the womb comes through the
          navel. New cells are made in the marrow of our bones. As the navel and
          bones picture the life flow of our bodies, so the navel and bones are a
          picture of our inner being. See  .    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Glorify God with all your wealth,honoring him with your firstfruits,with
        every increase that comes to you.
      comments: []
    - name: "10: Wisdom\u2019s Correction"
      title: "Wisdom\u2019s Correction"
      number: 10
      content: Then every dimension of your life will overflow with blessingsfrom
        an uncontainable source of inner joy!
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: My child, when the Lord God speaks to you,never take his words lightly,and
        never be upset when he corrects you.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For the Father\u2019s discipline comes onlyfrom his passionate love
        and pleasure for you.Even when it seems like his correction is harsh,it\u2019s
        still better than any father on earth gives to his child."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Blessings pour over the ones who find wisdom,for they have obtained
        living-understanding. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 3:13
        content: '  The Hebrew text here implies that wisdom gives the ability to
          take raw facts and draw right conclusions and meaning from them.    '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: As wisdom increases, a great treasure is imparted,greater than many
        bars of refined gold.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: It is a more valuable commodity than gold and gemstones, [[COMMENT(0)]]for
        there is nothing you desire that could compare to her.
      comments:
      - number: 3:15
        content: "  The Hebrew word translated here as \u201Cgemstones\u201D can
          also refer to rubies, coral, or pearls.    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Wisdom extends to you long life in one handand wealth and promotion
        [[COMMENT(0)]] in the other.Out of her mouth flows righteousness,and her
        words release both law and mercy. '
      comments:
      - number: 3:16
        content: "  Or \u201Chonor.\u201D      The Septuagint adds this last sentence,
          which is not found in the Hebrew.    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: The ways of wisdom are sweet,always drawing you into the place of
        wholeness. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 3:17
        content: "  The Hebrew word translated here as \u201Cwholeness\u201D can
          also mean \u201Cpeace\u201D or \u201Cprosperity.\u201D    "
    - name: "18: Wisdom\u2019s Blueprints"
      title: "Wisdom\u2019s Blueprints"
      number: 18
      content: Seeking for her brings the discovery of untold blessings,for she is
        the healing tree of life to those who taste her fruits. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 3:18
        content: '  Verses    and    are recited in contemporary Torah services as
          the Torah scroll is returned to the ark, where it is kept.    '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The Lord laid the earth\u2019s foundations with wisdom\u2019s blueprints.By
        his living-understanding all the universe came into being. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 3:19
        content: '  When compared with  , we can see that Wisdom is used as a title
          in Proverbs for the Living Wisdom, Jesus Christ. See  .    '
    - name: '20: Wisdom, Our Hiding Place'
      title: Wisdom, Our Hiding Place
      number: 20
      content: By his divine revelation he broke openthe hidden fountains of the
        deep,bringing secret springs to the surfaceas the mist of the night dripped
        down from heaven. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 3:20
        content: "  The dew is a metaphor for the Holy Spirit, who comes from the
          heavens and drenches us with God\u2019s presence. See  ;  ;  ;  .    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "My child, never drift off course from these two goals for your life:to
        walk in wisdom and to discover your purpose. [[COMMENT(0)]]Don\u2019t ever
        forget how they empower you."
      comments:
      - number: 3:21
        content: "  Like many Hebrew words, there are various possible translations.
          The word translated here as \u201Cpurpose\u201D can also mean \u201Cdiscretion,\u201D
          \u201Ccounsel,\u201D \u201Cmeditation,\u201D or \u201Cdiscernment.\u201D    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "For they strengthen you inside and outand inspire you to do what\u2019s
        right; [[COMMENT(0)]]you will be energized and refreshed by the healing they
        bring."
      comments:
      - number: 3:22
        content: "  Or \u201Cadorn your neck.\u201D The neck is a picture of our
          will and conscience.    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "They give you living hope to guide you,and not one of life\u2019s
        tests will cause you to stumble."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "You will sleep like a baby, safe and sound\u2014your rest will be
        sweet and secure."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: You will not be subject to terror, for it will not terrify you.Nor
        will the disrespectful be able to push you aside, [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 3:25
        content: '  As translated from the Septuagint.    '
    - name: '26: Wisdom in Relationships'
      title: Wisdom in Relationships
      number: 26
      content: because God is your confidence in times of crisis,keeping your heart
        at rest in every situation. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 3:26
        content: "  Or \u201Ckeeping your foot from being caught.\u201D    "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Why would you withhold payment on your debt [[COMMENT(0)]]when you
        have the ability to pay? Just do it! '
      comments:
      - number: 3:27
        content: "  The Septuagint is \u201CWhy would you withhold from the poor
          [those who need it]?\u201D      The Hebrew text here literally means \u201CDo
          not withhold wealth from its owners.\u201D See  .    "
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "When your friend comes to ask you for a favor,why would you say,
        \u201CPerhaps tomorrow,\u201Dwhen you have the money right there in your
        pocket?Help him today!"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Why would you hold a grudge [[COMMENT(0)]] in your hearttoward your
        neighbor who lives right next door?
      comments:
      - number: 3:29
        content: "  Or \u201Cplot evil.\u201D    "
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: And why would you quarrel with thosewho have done nothing wrong to
        you?Is that a chip on your shoulder? [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 3:30
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Don\u2019t act like those bullies or learn their ways."
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: Every violent thug is despised by the Lord,but every tender lover
        finds friendship with Godand will hear his intimate secrets. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 3:32
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "The wicked walk under God\u2019s constant curse,but the righteous
        walk under a stream of his blessing,for they seek to do what is right."
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "If you walk with the mockers you will learn to mock,but God\u2019s
        grace and favor flow to the meek. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 3:34
        content: '  See    and  .  '
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: Stubborn fools fill their lives with disgrace,but glory and honor
        rest upon the wise.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: A Father\u2019s Instruction"
      title: "A Father\u2019s Instruction"
      number: 1
      content: Listen to my correction, my sons,for I speak to you as your father.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]Let discernment enter your heartand you will grow wise with
        the understanding I impart.
      comments:
      - number: 4:1
        content: '  Read and study this entire chapter as though it were Jesus Christ
          speaking to you. He is the Father of Eternity, and we are called his sons.
          See    and  .    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: My revelation-truth [[COMMENT(0)]] is a gift to you,so remain faithful
        to my instruction.
      comments:
      - number: 4:2
        content: "  Literally \u201CTorah.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For I, too, was once the delight of my father [[COMMENT(0)]]and cherished
        by my mother\u2014their beloved  child."
      comments:
      - number: 4:3
        content: "  See    and  .      Or \u201Cunique.\u201D See  .    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then my father taught me, saying,\u201CNever forget my words.If you
        do everything that I teach you, you will reign in life.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 4:4
        content: '  The lessons of wisdom are meant to be passed on from parents
          to children.    '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So make wisdom your quest\u2014search for the revelation of life\u2019s
        meaning.Don\u2019t let what I say go in one ear and out the other."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Stick with wisdom and she will stick to you,protecting you throughout
        your days.She will rescue all those who passionately listen to her voice.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 4:6
        content: '  It is not enough to acquire wisdom; we must love her and listen
          wholeheartedly to her instruction.    '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Wisdom is the most valuable commodity\u2014so buy it!Revelation-knowledge
        is what you need\u2014so invest in it!"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Wisdom will exalt you when you exalt her truth. [[COMMENT(0)]]She
        will lead you to honor and favorwhen you live your life by her insights.
      comments:
      - number: 4:8
        content: "  The Septuagint says, \u201CBuild a fort for wisdom and she will
          lift you high.\u201D    "
    - name: '9: Two Pathways'
      title: Two Pathways
      number: 9
      content: "You will be adorned with beauty and grace, [[COMMENT(0)]]and wisdom\u2019s
        glory will wrap itself around you, making you victorious in the race."
      comments:
      - number: 4:9
        content: "  Literally \u201CShe will place a garland of grace on your head
          and a crown of beauty upon you.\u201D A garland and a crown are metaphors
          for what is awarded a victor in a race. See  .      Or \u201Cwisdom\u2019s
          laurel of glory shielding you.\u201D    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: My son, if you will take the time to stop and listen to meand embrace
        what I say,you will live a long and happy lifefull of understanding in every
        way.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "I have taken you by the hand in wisdom\u2019s ways,pointing you to
        the path of integrity."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Your progress will have no limits when you come along with me,and
        you will never stumble as you walk along the way.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So receive my correction [[COMMENT(0)]] no matter how hard it is
        to swallow,for wisdom will snap you back into place\u2014her words will be
        invigorating life to you."
      comments:
      - number: 4:13
        content: '  Wisdom will correct us and adjust our hearts to discipline. We
          must embrace the corrections of wisdom in order to mature spiritually.    '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Do not detour into darkness or even set foot on that path.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Stay away from it; don\u2019t even go there!"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: For troublemakers are restless if they are not involved in evil.They
        are not satisfied until they have brought someone harm.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "They feed on darkness and drinkuntil they\u2019re drunk on the wine
        of wickedness. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 4:17
        content: "  Or \u201Cviolence.\u201D    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: But the lovers of God walk on the highway of light, [[COMMENT(0)]]and
        their way shines brighter and brighteruntil the perfect day.
      comments:
      - number: 4:18
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe glow of sunlight.\u201D    "
    - name: '19: Healing Words'
      title: Healing Words
      number: 19
      content: "But the wicked walk in thick darkness,like those who travel in fog,and
        yet don\u2019t have a clue why they keep stumbling!"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Listen carefully, my dear child, to everything that I teach you,and
        pay attention to all that I have to say.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Fill your thoughts with my wordsuntil they penetrate deep into your
        spirit. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 4:21
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Then, as you unwrap my words, [[COMMENT(0)]]they will impart true
        life and radiant healthinto the very core of your being.
      comments:
      - number: 4:22
        content: "  Or \u201Cdiscover my words.\u201D    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: So above all, guard the affections of your heart, [[COMMENT(0)]]for
        they affect all that you are.Pay attention to the welfare of your innermost
        being,for from there flows the wellspring  of life.
      comments:
      - number: 4:23
        content: "  The Hebrew word    is the most common word for \u201Cheart.\u201D
          It includes our thoughts, our wills, our discernment, and our affections.     
          Although most translations have \u201Cthe issues of life,\u201D the Hebrew
          word    is actually \u201Cseasons,\u201D especially springtime. Out of
          your heart flow the seasons of life. It is our hearts, not our ages or
          circumstances, that shape the seasons of our lives. If our hearts are tender
          to God, we can live in perpetual springtime.    "
    - name: "24: Watch Where You\u2019re Going"
      title: "Watch Where You\u2019re Going"
      number: 24
      content: Avoid dishonest speech and pretentious words.Be free from using perverse
        words no matter what!
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Set your gaze on the path before you.With fixed purpose, looking
        straight ahead,ignore life\u2019s distractions. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 4:25
        content: '  Implied in the text. See  .  '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Watch where you\u2019re going!Stick to the path of truth,and the
        road will be safe and smooth before you."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Don\u2019t allow yourself to be sidetracked for even a momentor take
        the detour that leads to darkness."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Avoid Promiscuity'
      title: Avoid Promiscuity
      number: 1
      content: "Listen to me, my son,for I know what I\u2019m talking about.Listen
        carefully to my advice"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "so that wisdom and discernment will enter your heart,and then the
        words you speak will express what you\u2019ve learned."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Remember this:The lips of a seductress [[COMMENT(0)]] seem sweet like
        honey,and her smooth words are like music in your ears.
      comments:
      - number: 5:3
        content: "  Some Jewish expositors view this \u201Cseductress\u201D as a
          metaphor for heresy. She seduces, deceives, and drags to hell. For the
          believer, the seductress can be a picture of the false anointing of the
          religious spirit that attempts to seduce us, weaken our message, and rob
          the anointing of God from our ministries. Of course, there is also a clear
          and dire warning for all to stay sexually pure or face the consequences.    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But I promise you this:In the end all you\u2019ll be left with is
        a bitter conscience. [[COMMENT(0)]]For the sting of your sin will pierce
        your soul like a sword."
      comments:
      - number: 5:4
        content: "  Or \u201C  bitter as wormwood.\u201D See  .    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: She will ruin your life, drag you down to death,and lead you straight
        to hell. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 5:5
        content: "  Or \u201CSheol.\u201D This is the Aramaic and Hebrew word for
          the place of the dead. The Greeks called it Hades. Sheol is not eternal:
          it will be destroyed. See    and  .    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "She has prevented many from considering the paths of life.Yes, she
        will take you with her where you don\u2019t want to go,sliding down a slippery
        roadand not even realizing where the two of you will end up!"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Listen to me, young men,and don\u2019t forget this one thing I\u2019m
        telling you\u2014run away from her as fast as you can!"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Don\u2019t even go near the door of her houseunless you want to fall
        into her seduction."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "In disgrace you will relinquish your honor to another,and all your
        remaining years will be squandered\u2014given over to the cruel one. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 5:9
        content: '  This would be the devil, who torments the conscience as the result
          of this sin.    '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Why would you let strangers take away your strength [[COMMENT(0)]]while
        the labors of your house go to someone else?
      comments:
      - number: 5:10
        content: "  Or \u201Cwealth.\u201D This could also refer to spiritual strength
          and wealth.    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For when you grow old you will groan in anguish and shame [[COMMENT(0)]]as
        sexually transmitted diseases consume your body. '
      comments:
      - number: 5:11
        content: "  The Hebrew word translated here as \u201Cgroan\u201D is also
          used for the roar of a lion or the ocean\u2019s roar.      Implied in the
          context of the topic of sexual promiscuity. The Hebrew word here means
          \u201Cdiseases.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And then finally you\u2019ll admit that you were wrong and say,\u201CIf
        only I had listened to wisdom\u2019s voiceand not stubbornly demanded my
        own way,because my heart hated to be told what to do!"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Why didn\u2019t I take seriously the warning of my wise counselors?Why
        was I so stupid to think that I could get away with it?"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Sex Reserved for Marriage'
      title: Sex Reserved for Marriage
      number: 14
      content: "Now I\u2019m totally disgraced and my life is ruined!I\u2019m paying
        the price\u2014for the people of the congregation are now my judges.\u201D
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 5:14
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: My son, share your love with your wife alone.Drink from her well of
        pleasure and from no other.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Why would you have sex with a strangeror with anyone other than her?
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Reserve this pleasure for you and her alone and do not share it with
        another. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 5:17
        content: "  Because of the sudden change in the Hebrew text to the masculine
          gender (\u201Cstranger\u201D or \u201Canother\u201D), there is an inference
          that men having sex with men is forbidden, as well as sex with a woman
          who is not your wife.    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Your sex life will be blessed [[COMMENT(0)]]as you take joy and pleasure
        in the wife of your youth.
      comments:
      - number: 5:18
        content: '  The Hebrew phrase used here includes the word  , which is an
          obvious metaphor for the sex act. The root word for    can also refer to
          the eyes. It may be a poetic subtlety that your eyes should only be on
          your wife, not on the nakedness of another. See v.  .    '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Let her breasts be your satisfaction, [[COMMENT(0)]]and let her embrace 
        intoxicate you at all times.Be continually delighted and ravished with her
        love!
      comments:
      - number: 5:19
        content: "  The Hebrew includes a picturesque metaphor of the wife being
          like a \u201Cfriendly deer and a favored filly.\u201D      The Septuagint
          reads \u201Clet her share conversation with you.\u201D    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "My son, why would you be exhilarated by an adulteress\u2014by embracing
        a woman [[COMMENT(0)]] who is not yours?"
      comments:
      - number: 5:20
        content: "  Or \u201Cbreasts.\u201D  "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: For God sees everything you do and his eyes are wide openas he observes
        every single habit you have.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Beware that your sins don\u2019t overtake youand that the scars of
        your own conscience don\u2019tbecome the ropes that tie you up."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Those who choose wickedness die for lack of self-control,for their
        foolish ways lead them astray,carrying them away as hostages\u2014kidnapped
        captives robbed of destiny."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Words of Wisdom'
      title: Words of Wisdom
      number: 1
      content: "My son, if you cosign a loan for an acquaintanceand guarantee his
        debt,you\u2019ll be sorry that you ever did it!"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "You\u2019ll be trapped by your promiseand legally bound by the agreement.So
        listen carefully to my advice:"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Quickly get out of it if you possibly can!Swallow your pride, get
        over your embarrassment,and go tell your \u201Cfriend\u201D you want your
        name [[COMMENT(0)]] off that contract."
      comments:
      - number: 6:3
        content: "  There is an implication in the Hebrew that the one whose loan
          was cosigned for is no longer a friend. The Hebrew word can also be translated
          \u201Capostate.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Don\u2019t put it off, and don\u2019t rest until you get it done."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Life Lessons'
      title: Life Lessons
      number: 5
      content: "Rescue yourself from future pain [[COMMENT(0)]]and be free from it
        once and for all.You\u2019ll be so relieved that you did!  "
      comments:
      - number: 6:5
        content: "  The Hebrew word means \u201Ctrap.\u201D      The life lesson
          to learn is that even when considering something that seems to be good,
          there may be unexpected consequences that should be considered before obligating
          yourself.    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When you\u2019re feeling lazy,come and learn a lesson from this tale
        of the tiny ant.Yes, all you lazybones, come learnfrom the example of the
        ant and enter into wisdom."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The ants have no chief, no boss, no manager\u2014no one has to tell
        them what to do."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "You\u2019ll see them working and toiling all summer long,stockpiling
        their food in preparation for winter."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: So wake up, sleepyhead. How long will you lie there?When will you
        wake up and get out of bed?
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "If you keep nodding off and thinking, \u201CI\u2019ll do it later,\u201Dor
        say to yourself, \u201CI\u2019ll just sit back awhile and take it easy,\u201Djust
        watch how the future unfolds!"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "By making excuses you\u2019ll learn what it means to go without.Poverty
        will pounce on you like a bandit [[COMMENT(0)]]and move in as your roommate
        for life. "
      comments:
      - number: 6:11
        content: "  Or \u201Cvagabond.\u201D The Hebrew phrase here is literally
          translated \u201Cone who walks (away).\u201D      The life lesson from
          Solomon\u2019s parable is this: the ant only lives six months yet stores
          more food than it will ever consume. We should learn the wisdom of preparing
          for the future and frugality in the present. Don\u2019t put off for the
          future the preparations you should make today. Now is always better than
          later. Today is the day to choose what\u2019s right and serve the Lord.    "
    - name: '12-13: '
      title: 
      number: 12-13
      content: "Here\u2019s another life lesson to learnfrom observing wayward and
        wicked men. [[COMMENT(0)]]You can tell they are lawless.They\u2019re constant
        liars, proud deceivers,full of clever ploys and convincing plots. "
      comments:
      - number: "6:12\u201313"
        content: "  The Hebrew word translated \u201Cwayward and wicked man\u201D
          is actually \u201Ca man of Belial.\u201D This is a metaphor for a worthless
          man who worships other gods. The name Belial is found in numerous Dead
          Sea scrolls as a term for Satan.      The Hebrew gives a picture of those
          who \u201Cwink their eyes, shuffle their feet, and point their fingers.\u201D
          This is a figure of speech for the devious ways of the wicked.    "
    - name: '12-13: '
      title: 
      number: 12-13
      content: "Here\u2019s another life lesson to learnfrom observing wayward and
        wicked men. [[COMMENT(0)]]You can tell they are lawless.They\u2019re constant
        liars, proud deceivers,full of clever ploys and convincing plots. "
      comments:
      - number: "6:12\u201313"
        content: "  The Hebrew word translated \u201Cwayward and wicked man\u201D
          is actually \u201Ca man of Belial.\u201D This is a metaphor for a worthless
          man who worships other gods. The name Belial is found in numerous Dead
          Sea scrolls as a term for Satan.      The Hebrew gives a picture of those
          who \u201Cwink their eyes, shuffle their feet, and point their fingers.\u201D
          This is a figure of speech for the devious ways of the wicked.    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Their twisted thoughts are perverse,and they are always scheming to
        stir up trouble,and sowing strife with every step they take.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Seven Things God Hates'
      title: Seven Things God Hates
      number: 15
      content: "But when calamity comes knocking on their door,suddenly and without
        warning they\u2019re undone\u2014broken to bits, shattered, with no hope
        of healing. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 6:15
        content: "  The life lesson here is this: the clever and devious may look
          like they\u2019re getting ahead in life, but their path guarantees destruction,
          with no one to help them out of it.    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'There are six evils God truly hatesand a seventh [[COMMENT(0)]] that
        is an abomination to him:'
      comments:
      - number: 6:16
        content: '  The number seven is the number of fullness and completion. The
          poetic form here is stating that evil in its fullness is an abomination
          to God. The seven things are a description of the sin of man that stands
          in the temple of our bodies attempting to usurp God.    '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Putting others down while considering yourself superior,spreading
        lies and rumors,spilling the blood of the innocent,
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "plotting evil in your heart toward another,gloating over doing what\u2019s
        plainly wrong,"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: spouting lies in false testimony,and stirring up strife between friends.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]These are entirely despicable to God!
      comments:
      - number: 6:19
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201Cdeception among brothers.\u201D    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "My son, obey your father\u2019s godly instructionand follow your
        mother\u2019s life-giving teaching. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 6:20
        content: '  For the New Testament believer, our mother is the church, who
          nurtures us and feeds us life-giving words. See  .    '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Fill your heart with their adviceand let your life be shaped by what
        they\u2019ve taught you. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 6:21
        content: "  Or \u201CBind their words on your heart and tie them around your
          neck.\u201D    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Their wisdom will guide you wherever you goand keep you from bringing
        harm to yourself.Their instruction will whisper to you at every sunriseand
        direct you through a brand-new day.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Truth or Consequences'
      title: Truth or Consequences
      number: 23
      content: For truth [[COMMENT(0)]] is a bright beam of lightshining into every
        area of your life,instructing and correcting you to discover the ways to
        godly living.
      comments:
      - number: 6:23
        content: "  Or \u201CTorah.\u201D    "
    - name: '24-25: '
      title: 
      number: 24-25
      content: "Truth will protect you from immoralityand from the promiscuity of
        another man\u2019s wife.Your heart won\u2019t be enticed by her flatteries
        [[COMMENT(0)]]or lust over her beauty\u2014nor will her suggestive ways conquer
        you."
      comments:
      - number: "6:24\u201325"
        content: "  Or \u201CDon\u2019t let her captivate you with her fluttering
          eyelids.\u201D    "
    - name: '24-25: '
      title: 
      number: 24-25
      content: "Truth will protect you from immoralityand from the promiscuity of
        another man\u2019s wife.Your heart won\u2019t be enticed by her flatteries
        [[COMMENT(0)]]or lust over her beauty\u2014nor will her suggestive ways conquer
        you."
      comments:
      - number: "6:24\u201325"
        content: "  Or \u201CDon\u2019t let her captivate you with her fluttering
          eyelids.\u201D    "
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Prostitutes reduce a man to poverty, [[COMMENT(0)]]and the adulteress
        steals your soul\u2014she may even cost you your life! "
      comments:
      - number: 6:26
        content: "  Or \u201Cto beg for a loaf of bread.\u201D      The Hebrew phrase
          here is literally translated \u201Cshe hunts for your precious soul.\u201D    "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: For how can a man light his pants on fire and not be burned?
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Can he walk over hot coals of fire [[COMMENT(0)]] and not blister
        his feet?
      comments:
      - number: 6:28
        content: '  A picture of the lusts of the flesh.    '
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "What makes you think that you can sleep with another man\u2019s wifeand
        not get caught?Do you really think you\u2019ll get away with it?Don\u2019t
        you know it will ruin your life?"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: You can almost excuse a thief if he steals to feed his own family.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But if he\u2019s caught, he still has to pay back what he stole sevenfold;his
        punishment and fine will cost him greatly."
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Don\u2019t be so stupid as to thinkyou can get away with your adultery.It
        will destroy your life, [[COMMENT(0)]] and you\u2019ll pay the pricefor the
        rest of your days."
      comments:
      - number: 6:32
        content: "  Or \u201CThe destroyer of your soul will do this.\u201D  "
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "You\u2019ll discover what humiliation, shame,and disgrace are all
        about,for no one will ever let you forget what you\u2019ve done."
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "A husband\u2019s jealousy makes a man furious;he won\u2019t spare
        you when he comes to take revenge."
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Try all you want to talk your way out of it\u2014offer him a bribe
        and see if you can manipulate himwith your money.Nothing will turn him asidewhen
        he comes to you with vengeance in his eyes!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Wisdom, Your True Love'
      title: Wisdom, Your True Love
      number: 1
      content: Stick close to my instruction, my son,and follow all my advice.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: If you do what I say you will live well.Guard your life with my revelation-truth,for
        my teaching is as precious as your eyesight. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 7:2
        content: "  Or \u201Clike you would the pupil of your eye.\u201D Literally
          \u201Cthe little man of the eye,\u201D which is a figure of speech for
          your most prized possession.    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Treasure my instructions, and cherish them within your heart. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 7:3
        content: "  Or \u201CWrite them upon the tablets of your heart.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Say to wisdom, \u201CI love you,\u201Dand to understanding, \u201CYou\u2019re
        my sweetheart.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CMay the two of you protect me, and may we never be apart!\u201DFor
        they will keep you from the adulteress,with her smooth words meant to seduce
        your heart."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Looking out the window of my house one day
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I noticed among the mindless crowda simple, na\xEFve young man who
        was about to go astray."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "There he was, walking down the street.Then he turned the corner,going
        on his way hurrying to the house of the harlot\u2014the woman he had planned
        to meet."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: There he was in the twilight as darkness fell,convinced no one was
        watchingas he entered the black shadows of hell. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 7:9
        content: '  Implied from v.  .    '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "That\u2019s when their rendezvous began.A woman of the night appeared,dressed
        to kill the strength of any man.She was decked out as a harlot, pursuing
        her amorous plan."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Her voice was seductive, rebellious, and boisterousas she wandered
        far from what\u2019s right."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Her type can be found soliciting on street cornerson just about any
        night.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "She wrapped her arms around the senseless young manand held him tight\u2014she
        enticed him with kisses that seemed so right.Then, with insolence, she whispered
        in his ear,"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CCome with me. It\u2019ll be all right.I\u2019ve got everything
        we need for a feast.I\u2019ll cook you a wonderful dinner. [[COMMENT(0)]]So
        here I am\u2014I\u2019m all yours!"
      comments:
      - number: 7:14
        content: "  Or \u201Coffered peace offerings and paid my vows [in the temple].\u201D
          This is a way of saying, \u201CI have lots of meat left over from the sacrifices
          I\u2019ve offered, enough for a great meal.\u201D    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "You\u2019re the very one I\u2019ve looked for,the one I knew I wanted
        from the moment I saw you.That\u2019s why I\u2019ve come out here tonight,so
        I could meet a man just like you. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 7:15
        content: '  Compared to  , this seems to be a parodic reversal of the Shulamite
          who goes out into the city to seek a man, and when she finds him, embraces
          him. This account of the harlot seems to be the converse of the theme of
          Song of Songs.    '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "I\u2019ve spread my canopy bed with coverings,lovely multicolored
        Egyptian linensready for you to lie down on."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "I\u2019ve sprinkled the sheets with intoxicating perfumemade from
        myrrh, aloes, and sweet cinnamon. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 7:17
        content: '  Although these spices are found in the sacred anointing oil,
          the adulteress (religious system) has only a false anointing with no true
          power.    '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Come, let\u2019s get comfortable and take pleasure in each otherand
        make love all night!"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "There\u2019s no one home, for my husband\u2019s away on business."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "He left home loaded with money to spend,so don\u2019t worry.He won\u2019t
        be back until another month ends.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 7:20
        content: "  Or \u201CHe left with a bag of money and won\u2019t be back until
          the new moon.\u201D    "
    - name: '21-22: '
      title: 
      number: 21-22
      content: He was swayed by her sophistication,enticed by her longing embrace.She
        led him down the wayward path right into sin and disgrace.Quickly he went
        astray, with no cluewhere he was truly headed,taken like a dumb ox alongside
        the butcher.She was like a venomous snake coiled to strike,so she set her
        fangs into him! [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: "7:21\u201322"
        content: "  The last sentence in this verse is arguably difficult to translate,
          with many variant options. The Aramaic is \u201Ctaken like a dog to captivity.\u201D
          The Hebrew can be translated \u201Cbounding like a stag to a trap.\u201D
          Other ancient Jewish commentaries refer to this portion as \u201Crushing
          like a venomous snake to discipline the foolish one,\u201D meaning that
          with the swiftness of a snake striking its prey, a fool lunges into his
          own destruction.    "
    - name: '21-22: '
      title: 
      number: 21-22
      content: He was swayed by her sophistication,enticed by her longing embrace.She
        led him down the wayward path right into sin and disgrace.Quickly he went
        astray, with no cluewhere he was truly headed,taken like a dumb ox alongside
        the butcher.She was like a venomous snake coiled to strike,so she set her
        fangs into him! [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: "7:21\u201322"
        content: "  The last sentence in this verse is arguably difficult to translate,
          with many variant options. The Aramaic is \u201Ctaken like a dog to captivity.\u201D
          The Hebrew can be translated \u201Cbounding like a stag to a trap.\u201D
          Other ancient Jewish commentaries refer to this portion as \u201Crushing
          like a venomous snake to discipline the foolish one,\u201D meaning that
          with the swiftness of a snake striking its prey, a fool lunges into his
          own destruction.    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He\u2019s like a man about to be executed with an arrowright through
        his heart\u2014like a bird that flies into the net,unaware of what\u2019s
        about to happen."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So listen to me, you young men.You\u2019d better take my words seriously!"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Control your sexual urges and guard your hearts against lust.Don\u2019t
        let your passions get out of handand don\u2019t lock your eyes onto a beautiful
        woman.Why would you want to even get closeto temptation and seduction,to
        have an affair with her?"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "She has pierced the souls of multitudes of men\u2014many mighty ones
        have fallenand have been brought down by her. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 7:26
        content: "  The Aramaic is even more descriptive: \u201CShe has slain a multitude
          of mighty ones; they\u2019ve all been killed by her.\u201D    "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "If you\u2019re looking for the road to hell,just go looking for her
        house! [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 7:27
        content: "  This parable (vv.  ) not only warns against the obvious evils
          of adultery and immorality, but also serves as a warning to the anointed
          young men in ministry not to be seduced by the religious system. Wisdom
          looks from the window (revelation and insight\u2014see  ) of her house
          (the true church of Jesus) and sees a young man (not fully mature\u2014see 
          ) who has placed himself in the path of sin. This made him vulnerable to
          the seduction of the \u201Charlot\u201D system of a works-based religion
          that enticed him into her bed (partnership, covering, and ordination with
          her and her system\u2014see  ) covered with Egyptian linens (Egypt is a
          picture of the world system that holds people in bondage). She is loud
          and stubborn (the old self-life never dealt with) and will not remain in
          her house (the true church of Jesus). She lives in the darkness of compromise
          and her ways are the ways of death. She doesn\u2019t remain faithful to
          her husband (the Bridegroom-God). The two women of Proverbs are the harlot
          mentioned here and the virtuous woman found in chapter  , who speak of
          two systems of worship. One is true and virtuous; the other is false and
          seductive.  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1-3: Wisdom Calling'
      title: Wisdom Calling
      number: 1-3
      content: "Can\u2019t you hear the voice of Wisdom? [[COMMENT(0)]]From the top
        of the mountains of influenceshe speaks into the gateways of the glorious
        city. At the place where pathways merge,at the entrance of every portal,there
        she stands, ready to impart understanding,shouting aloud to all who enter,preaching
        her sermon to those who will listen. "
      comments:
      - number: "8:1\u20133"
        content: "  Wisdom is personified throughout the book of Proverbs. Lady Wisdom
          is a figure of speech for God himself, who invites us to receive the best
          way to live, the excellent and noble way of life found in Jesus Christ.
          Jesus is wisdom personified, for he was anointed with the Spirit of Wisdom.
          See  ;  ;  .      As translated from the Aramaic. The church is also a
          gateway, the house of God, the portal to heaven, and as Jesus calls it,
          a \u201Ccity that stands on a hilltop\u201D (see  ). Christ is the head
          of the church, where the wisdom of God is revealed. See    and  .     
          In chapter    it was the harlot calling out to the simple; here it is Lady
          Wisdom. True wisdom is easy to find\u2014we only have to listen to her
          voice. Though it comes from above, it is found on street level. Creation
          and conscience are two voices that speak to our hearts. To discover wisdom,
          we don\u2019t need a brilliant intellect but a tender, attentive heart.    "
