    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CI\u2019m calling to you, sons of Adam,yes, and to you daughters
        as well."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Listen to me and you will be prudent and wise.For even the foolish
        and feeble can receive an understanding heartthat will change their inner
        being.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: The meaning of my words will release within you revelationfor you
        to reign in life. [[COMMENT(0)]]My lyrics will empower you to live by what
        is right.
      comments:
      - number: 8:6
        content: "  The Hebrew word is literally translated as \u201Cprincely\u201D
          or \u201Cnoble\u201D things. The implication is that these words of wisdom
          are for ruling and reigning in life.    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "For everything I say is unquestionably true,and I refuse to endure
        the lies of lawlessness\u2014my words will never lead you astray."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: All the declarations of my mouth can be trusted;they contain no twisted
        logic or perversion of the truth.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: All my words are clear and straightforward to everyonewho possesses
        spiritual understanding.If you have an open mind, you will receive revelation-knowledge.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "My wise correction is more valuable than silver or gold.The finest
        gold is nothing compared to the revelation-knowledgeI can impart.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Wisdom is so priceless that it exceeds the value of any jewel. [[COMMENT(0)]]Nothing
        you could wish for can equal her.
      comments:
      - number: 8:11
        content: "  Literally \u201Ccorals\u201D or \u201Cpearls.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CFor I am Wisdom, and I am shrewd and intelligent.I have at
        my disposal living-understandingto devise a plan for your life. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 8:12
        content: "  Or \u201Cto discover clever inventions.\u201D    "
    - name: '13: The Power of Wisdom'
      title: The Power of Wisdom
      number: 13
      content: "Wisdom pours into youwhen you begin to hate every form of evil in
        your life,for that\u2019s what worship and fearing God is all about.Then
        you will discoverthat your pompous pride and perverse speechare the very
        ways of wickedness that I hate!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CYou will find true success when you find me,for I have insight
        into wise plans that are designed just for you.I hold in my hands living-understanding,
        [[COMMENT(0)]] courage, and strength."
      comments:
      - number: 8:14
        content: "  Or \u201CI am living-understanding.\u201D    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: I empower kings to reign and rulers to make laws that are just. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 8:15
        content: '  We have been made kings and priestly rulers by the grace of redemption.    '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: I empower princes to rise and take dominion,and generous ones to govern
        the earth. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 8:16
        content: "  As translated from many Hebrew manuscripts and the Septuagint.
          Other Hebrew manuscripts have \u201Cand all nobles who govern justly.\u201D
          The word    can also be translated \u201Cgenerous ones.\u201D    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: I will show my love to those who passionately love me. [[COMMENT(0)]]For
        they will search and search continually until they find me.
      comments:
      - number: 8:17
        content: '  Wisdom is not found by the halfhearted. One must love wisdom
          to gain it. A superficial desire will yield only a superficial knowledge.    '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Unending wealth and glorycome to those who discover where I dwell.The
        riches of righteousness and a long, satisfying lifewill be given to them.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 8:18
        content: "  Or \u201Criches and righteousness.\u201D The phrase \u201Ca long,
          satisfying life\u201D is from the Aramaic.    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: What I impart has greater worth than gold and treasure,and the increase
        I bring benefits more than a windfall of income.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: I lead you into the ways of righteousnessto discover the paths of
        true justice.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Wisdom in the Beginning'
      title: Wisdom in the Beginning
      number: 21
      content: "Those who love me gain great wealth [[COMMENT(0)]] and a glorious
        inheritance,and I will fill their lives with treasures.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 8:21
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201CI will leave great hope as an inheritance
          to my friends.\u201D    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CIn the beginning I was there,for God possessed me [[COMMENT(0)]]
        even before he created the universe."
      comments:
      - number: 8:22
        content: "  The Aramaic and the Septuagint read \u201CThe Lord created me
          at the beginning.\u201D The Hebrew verb translated here as \u201Cpossessed\u201D
          has two basic meanings. One is \u201Cacquired,\u201D the other is \u201Ccreated.\u201D
          Poetically, it is a statement that the existence of Wisdom (Christ) was
          not independent of God at creation but was manifested and possessed by
          God as he created all things. Otherwise, it would sound like God was without
          wisdom before he created it.    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: From eternity past I was set in place,before the world began.I was
        anointed [[COMMENT(0)]] from the beginning.
      comments:
      - number: 8:23
        content: "  The Hebrew word translated \u201Canointed\u201D here literally
          means \u201Cpoured out\u201D and is often used to describe the anointing
          oil poured out over a king.    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Before the oceans depths were poured out,and before there were any
        glorious fountainsoverflowing with water, [[COMMENT(0)]]I was there, dancing! '
      comments:
      - number: 8:24
        content: "  The Hebrew uses the word  , which means \u201Cglory,\u201D to
          describe the fountains. It could also be translated \u201Cfountains of
          glory\u201D or \u201Cglorious fountains.\u201D      Many translations have
          \u201CI was born [or brought forth].\u201D The Hebrew word for \u201Cborn\u201D
          is taken from a word that means \u201Cto kick and twirl\u201D or \u201Cto
          dance.\u201D    "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Even before one mountain had been sculptedor one hill raised up,I
        was already there, dancing!
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: When he created the earth, the fields,even the first atom of dust,I
        was already there.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: When he hung the tapestry of the heavensand stretched out the horizon
        of the earth,
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: when the clouds and skies were set in placeand the subterranean fountains
        began to flow strong,I was already there.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "When he set in place the pillars of the earthand spoke the decrees
        of the seas,commanding the wavesso that they wouldn\u2019t overstep their
        boundaries,"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "I was there, close to the Creator\u2019s side [[COMMENT(0)]] as his
        master artist. Daily he was filled with delight in meas I playfully rejoiced
        before him. "
      comments:
      - number: 8:30
        content: "  See  .      Or \u201Carchitect.\u201D      The Hebrew word translated
          here as \u201Crejoiced\u201D can also be translated as \u201Cjoyfully playing\u201D
          or \u201Claughing.\u201D    "
    - name: '31: Wisdom Worth Waiting For'
      title: Wisdom Worth Waiting For
      number: 31
      content: "I laughed and played,so happy with what he had made,while finding
        my delight in the children of men.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 8:31
        content: '  What a beautiful picture we find here of Wisdom (Christ), who
          finds his fulfillment in us. See  ;  ;  ;  ;  .    '
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CSo listen, my sons and daughters, to everything I tell you,for
        nothing will bring you more joy than following my ways."
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Listen to my counsel,for my instruction will enlighten you.You\u2019ll
        be wise not to ignore it."
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "If you wait at wisdom\u2019s doorway, [[COMMENT(0)]]longing to hear
        a word for every day,joy will break forth within you as you listen for what
        I\u2019ll say."
      comments:
      - number: 8:34
        content: "  Or \u201CGuard the door of my entrances.\u201D    "
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: For the fountain of life pours into you every time that you find me,and
        this is the secret of growing in the delightand the favor of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "But those who stumble and miss me will be sorry they did!For ignoring
        what I have to say will bring harm to your own soul.Those who hate me are
        simply flirting with death!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 8:36
        content: '  To hate wisdom is not only a sign of stupidity, but it is also
          a mark of depravity.  '
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Wisdom\u2019s Feast"
      title: "Wisdom\u2019s Feast"
      number: 1
      content: 'Wisdom [[COMMENT(0)]] has built herself a palace upon seven pillars
        to keep it secure. '
      comments:
      - number: 9:1
        content: "  Lady Wisdom is a poetic personification representing Christ,
          the Wisdom of God (). This is a classic form of a synecdoche. The Hebrew
          word    (\u201Cwisdom\u201D) can also mean \u201Csacred sense.\u201D It
          is the understanding and insight given only by God.      There is a fascinating
          word play in the Hebrew text. The verb meaning \u201Cto build\u201D and
          the word translated \u201Cson\u201D come from the same root. \u201CBuild\u201D
          is    and \u201Cson\u201D is  . The house Wisdom is building is a son.
          You and I are sons of God who are being built into a spiritual house. There
          is also a verb in the Hebrew for \u201Chewn\u201D (as in stones). We are
          living stones raised up to be God\u2019s temple. See  ;  ;  ;  .      The
          seven pillars of wisdom (plural, \u201Cwisdoms\u201D) point us to the seven
          days of creation, the seven spirits of God, and the seven components of
          heavenly wisdom given in  .    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "She has made ready a banquet feastand the sacrifice has been killed.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]She has mingled her wine, and the table\u2019s all set. "
      comments:
      - number: 9:2
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. The sacrifice points us to Calvary.
          Wisdom\u2019s pillar is a cross. The Hebrew phrase here literally means
          \u201Cshe has prepared her meat.\u201D      Wisdom\u2019s feast will teach
          us the ways of God. We feed our hearts on revelation-truth that transforms
          us; then we implement with wise strategies the understanding we have learned
          at the feasting table.    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "She has sent out her maidens,crying out from the high place,inviting
        everyone to comeand eat until they\u2019re full."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CWhoever wants to know me and receive my wisdom,"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: come and dine at my table and drink of my wine.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Lay aside your simple thoughts and leave your paths behind.Agree
        with my ways, live in my truth,and you will find righteousness.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "If you try to correct an arrogant cynic,expect an angry insult in
        return.And if you try to confront an evil man,don\u2019t be surprised if
        all you get is a slap in the face!"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So don\u2019t even bother to correct a mocker,for he\u2019ll only
        hate you for it.But go ahead and correct the wise;they\u2019ll love you even
        more. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 9:8
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Teach a wise man what is rightand he\u2019ll grow even wiser.Instruct
        the lovers of Godand they\u2019ll learn even more."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The starting point for acquiring wisdomis to be consumed with awe
        as you worship <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>.To receive the revelation of
        the Holy One, [[COMMENT(0)]]you must come to the one who has living-understanding.
      comments:
      - number: 9:10
        content: "  Literally \u201Choly ones.\u201D    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Wisdom will extend your life,making every year more fruitful than
        the one before.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: A Spirit Named Foolish'
      title: A Spirit Named Foolish
      number: 12
      content: So it is to your advantage to be wise.But to ignore the counsel of
        wisdomis to invite trouble into your life. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 9:12
        content: "  The Aramaic adds here \u201CThe liar feeds on the wind and chases
          fantasies, for he has forsaken what is true to travel in a barren wilderness;
          forgetting the right paths, he leaves his own vineyard to walk with thirst
          and gather nothing.\u201D The Septuagint adds here \u201CIf you forsake
          folly you will reign forever. Seek discretion and your understanding will
          bring you knowledge.\u201D    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "There is a spirit named Foolish,who is boisterous and brash;she\u2019s
        seductive and restless."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: And there she sits at the gateway to the high places,on her throne
        overlooking the city.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'She preaches to all who walk by herwho are clueless as to what is
        happening: [[COMMENT(0)]]'
      comments:
      - number: 9:15
        content: "  Or \u201Cwho are walking straight ahead on their paths.\u201D    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CCome home with me.\u201DShe invites those who are easily led
        astray, saying,"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CIllicit sex is the best sex of all.Our secret affair will be
        sweeter than all others.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 9:17
        content: "  The Hebrew phrase here literally means \u201CStolen waters are
          sweet, and bread eaten in secret is pleasant.\u201D This is an obvious
          metaphor of finding sexual pleasure with someone other than your spouse
          and trying to get away with it. Finding pleasure in your relationship with
          your spouse is like drinking from a pure, clean fountain. But stolen water
          from someone else\u2019s fountain is yielding to foolishness. Adultery
          is always sin.    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Little do they know when they answer her callthat she dwells among
        the spirits of the dead,and all her guests soon become citizens of hell!
        [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 9:18
        content: "  Older Aramaic and Septuagint manuscripts add a verse here not
          found in the Hebrew: \u201CBut turn away; linger not in the place or even
          look at her. Don\u2019t drink from a strange fountain. Abstain and drink
          not from an alien fountain, so that you will enjoy a long life.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Wisdom for Today'
      title: Wisdom for Today
      number: 1
      content: 'The wisdom of Solomon: [[COMMENT(0)]]When wisdom comes to a son,joy
        comes to a father.When a son turns from wisdom,a mother grieves.'
      comments:
      - number: 10:1
        content: "  The title of this section starting with    indicates a different
          form. Solomon\u2019s four hundred sayings of wisdom fill this section,
          going through  . This compilation is an assorted collection of proverbs
          that is not easily outlined but is profound in its scope.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Gaining wealth through dishonesty [[COMMENT(0)]] is no gain at all.But
        honesty brings you a lasting happiness. '
      comments:
      - number: 10:2
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe treasures of wickedness.\u201D      Or \u201CRighteousness
          [honesty] delivers you from death.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The Lord satisfies the longings of all his lovers, [[COMMENT(0)]]but
        he withholds from the wicked what their souls crave. '
      comments:
      - number: 10:3
        content: "  Or \u201Csatisfies the souls of the righteous.\u201D      The
          Aramaic is \u201Cthe property of the evil he demolishes.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Slackers will know what it means to be poor,while the hard worker
        becomes wealthy.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Know the importance of the season you\u2019re inand a wise son you
        will be.But what a waste when an incompetent sonsleeps through his day of
        opportunity! [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 10:5
        content: "  Or \u201CTo gather in the summer is to be a wise son, but to
          sleep through the harvest is a disgrace.\u201D    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: The lover of God is enriched beyond belief,but the evil man only curses
        his luck. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 10:6
        content: "  The Hebrew is ambiguous and is literally translated \u201Cthe
          mouth of the wicked covers violence.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The reputation of the righteousbecomes a sweet memorial to him,while
        the wicked life only leaves a rotten stench. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 10:7
        content: "  Some Hebrew manuscripts and the Aramaic read \u201Cthe name of
          the wicked will be extinguished.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The heart of the wise will easily accept instruction.But those who
        do all the talkingare too busy to listen and learn.They\u2019ll just keep
        stumbling aheadinto the mess they created."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: The one who walks in integrity [[COMMENT(0)]]will experience a fearless
        confidence in life,but the one who is deviouswill eventually be exposed.
      comments:
      - number: 10:9
        content: "  Or \u201Cinnocence.\u201D The Aramaic is \u201CHe who walks in
          perfection walks in hope.\u201D    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The troublemaker always has a clever planand won\u2019t look you
        in the eye,but the one who speaks correction honestlycan be trusted to make
        peace. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 10:10
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint. The Hebrew is \u201Cthe babbling
          fool comes to ruin.\u201D    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The teachings of the lovers of God are likeliving truth flowing from
        the fountain of life,but the words of the wickedhide an ulterior motive.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 10:11
        content: "  Or \u201Chide violence.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Hatred keeps old quarrels alive, [[COMMENT(0)]]but love draws a veil
        over every insult and finds a way to make sin disappear.
      comments:
      - number: 10:12
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201CHatred stirs up judgment.\u201D      Love
          will cover up offenses against us, but never our own offenses.    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Words of wisdom flow from the one with true discernment.But to the
        heartless, words of wisdombecome like rods beating their backside.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Wise men don\u2019t divulge all that they know, [[COMMENT(0)]]but
        chattering fools blurt out wordsthat bring them to the brink of ruin."
      comments:
      - number: 10:14
        content: "  Or \u201CThose who are wise store up knowledge [like treasure].\u201D    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "A rich man\u2019s wealth becomes like a citadel of strength, [[COMMENT(0)]]but
        the poverty of the poor leaves their security in shambles."
      comments:
      - number: 10:15
        content: "  Or \u201Chis fortified city.\u201D    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: The lovers of God earn their wages for a life of righteousness,but
        the wages of the wicked are squandered on a life of sin. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 10:16
        content: "  Or \u201Ctheir harvest of wickedness.\u201D    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "If you readily receive correction,you are walking on the path to
        life.But if you reject rebuke,you\u2019re guaranteed to go astray. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 10:17
        content: "  The Aramaic is even more blunt: \u201CReject rebuke and you\u2019re
          a moron!\u201D    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "The one who hides his hatred while pretending to be your friendis
        nothing but a liar.But the one who slanders you behind your backproves that
        he\u2019s a fool, never to be trusted."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "If you keep talking, it won\u2019t be longbefore you\u2019re saying
        something really wrong.Prove you\u2019re wise from the very start\u2014just
        bite your tongue and be strong!"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: The teachings of the godly ones are like pure silver,bringing words
        of redemption to others, [[COMMENT(0)]]but the heart of the wicked is corrupt.
      comments:
      - number: 10:20
        content: "  Or \u201CThe tongue of the just is like choice silver.\u201D
          Silver is a metaphor for redemption.    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: The lovers of God feed many with their teachings, [[COMMENT(0)]]but
        the foolish ones starve themselvesfor lack of an understanding heart.
      comments:
      - number: 10:21
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201CThe lips of the righteous multiply mercy.\u201D    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: True enrichment comes from the blessing of the Lord,with rest and
        contentment [[COMMENT(0)]] in knowingthat it all comes from him.
      comments:
      - number: 10:22
        content: "  Or \u201Cwith no labor or sorrow attached.\u201D    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: The fool [[COMMENT(0)]] finds fun in planning to do wrong,but the
        wise delight in having discernment.
      comments:
      - number: 10:23
        content: "  The word translated \u201Cfool\u201D means \u201Cmoron\u201D
          in the Aramaic.    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: The lawless are haunted by their fearsand what they dread will come
        upon them, [[COMMENT(0)]]but the longings of the lovers of God will all be
        fulfilled.
      comments:
      - number: 10:24
        content: '  This speaks of the consequences of sin. There is a Judge who
          sees all that we do and will call us to account one day.    '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: The wicked are blown away by every stormy wind.But when a catastrophe
        comes,the lovers of God have a secure anchor.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "To trust a lazy person to get a job donewill be as irritating as
        smoke in your eyes\u2014as enjoyable as a toothache!"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Living in the worship and awe of Godwill bring you many years of contented
        living.So how could the wicked ever expect to have a long, happy life?
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Lovers of God have a joyful feast of gladness,but the ungodly see
        their hopes vanish right before their eyes.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: The beautiful ways of God are a safe resting placefor those who have
        integrity. [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>  </smallcaps>But to those who work wickednessthe
        ways of God spell doom.
      comments:
      - number: 10:29
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201CThe way of  is power to the perfect.\u201D    "
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "God\u2019s lover can never be greatly shaken.But the wicked will
        never inheritthe covenant blessings. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 10:30
        content: "  Or \u201Cland.\u201D This is metaphor for all of the covenantal
          blessings.  "
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: The teachings of the righteous are loaded with wisdom,but the words
        of the evil ones are crooked and perverse.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: Words that bring delight pour from the lips of the godly,but the words
        of the wicked are duplicitous.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Living in Righteousness'
      title: Living in Righteousness
      number: 1
      content: 'Dishonest business practice [[COMMENT(0)]]is something that <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>
        truly hates.But it pleases him when we apply the right standardsof measurement. '
      comments:
      - number: 11:1
        content: "  The Hebrew phrase here literally means \u201Cscales of deception
          [false balances].\u201D      The Hebrew phrase here literally means \u201Ca
          perfect stone.\u201D Stones were used as the legitimate weights of balance.
          Jesus is the perfect stone. See  .    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "When you act with presumption,convinced that you\u2019re right,don\u2019t
        be surprised if you fall flat on your face!But humility leads to wisdom."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Integrity will lead you to success,but treachery will destroy your
        dreams.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "When judgment day comes,all the wealth of the world won\u2019t help
        you one bit.So be rich in righteousness,for that\u2019s the only thing that
        can save you in death."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Those with good character walk on a smooth path,with no detour or
        deviation.But the wicked keep falling because of their own wickedness.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Integrity will keep a good man from falling.But the unbeliever is
        trapped,held captive to his sinful desires.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: When an evil man dies, all hope is lost,for his misplaced confidence
        goes in the coffin,buried along with him.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The righteous are snatched away from trouble,and the wicked show up
        in their place. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 11:8
        content: '  Haman is a classic example of this principle. See  ;  .    '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: The teachings of hypocrites can destroy you,but revelation-knowledge
        will rescue the righteous. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 11:9
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe righteous will be strengthened.\u201D    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The blessing that rests on the righteousreleases strength and favor
        to the entire city, [[COMMENT(0)]]but shouts of joy will be heard when the
        wicked one dies.
      comments:
      - number: 11:10
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic and the Septuagint.    '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The blessing of favor resting upon the righteousinfluences a city
        to lift it higher, [[COMMENT(0)]]but wicked leaders tear it apart by their
        words.
      comments:
      - number: 11:11
        content: '  Jesus describes the church as a city. See  .    '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: To quarrel with a neighbor is senseless. [[COMMENT(0)]]Bite your tongue;
        be wise and keep quiet!
      comments:
      - number: 11:12
        content: "  Or \u201CTo disparage your neighbor is being heartless.\u201D    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "You can\u2019t trust gossipers with a secret;they\u2019ll just go
        blab it all.Put your confidence instead in a trusted friend,for he will be
        faithful to keep it in confidence."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: People lose their way without wise leadership,but a nation succeeds
        and stands in victorywhen it has many good counselors to guide it.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: The evil man will do harm when confronted by a righteous man,because
        he hates those who await good news. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 11:15
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic and the Septuagint. The Hebrew
          is \u201CYou\u2019ll be ruined if you cosign for a stranger, and a hater
          of handshakes will be safe.\u201D    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'A gracious, generous womanwill be honored with a splendid [[COMMENT(0)]]
        reputation,but the woman who hates the truthlives with disgrace  and is surrounded
        by menwho are cutthroats, only greedy for money. '
      comments:
      - number: 11:16
        content: "  Or \u201Cglorious.\u201D      As translated from the older Aramaic
          and Septuagint texts, but not included in newer Hebrew manuscripts. There
          is an additional line added by the Aramaic and the Septuagint: \u201CThe
          lazy will lack, but the diligent support themselves financially.\u201D     
          The Septuagint is \u201Cthe diligent obtain wealth.\u201D    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: A man of kindness attracts favor,while a cruel man attracts nothing
        but trouble. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 11:17
        content: "  The Hebrew text indicates this trouble could be physical, related
          to one\u2019s health.    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Evil people may get a short-term gain, [[COMMENT(0)]]but to sow seeds
        of righteousnesswill bring a true and lasting reward.
      comments:
      - number: 11:18
        content: "  Or \u201Cwages of deception.\u201D    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: A son of righteousness [[COMMENT(0)]] experiences the abundant life,but
        the one who pursues evil hurries to his own death.
      comments:
      - number: 11:19
        content: "  As translated from one Hebrew manuscript, the Aramaic, and the
          Septuagint. Most Hebrew manuscripts have \u201CThe one who pursues righteousness.\u201D    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The Lord can\u2019t stand the stubborn heart bent toward evil,but
        he treasures those whose ways are pure. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 11:20
        content: "  Or \u201Cwholehearted.\u201D    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Assault your neighbor and you will certainly be punished, [[COMMENT(0)]]but
        God will rescue the children of the godly.
      comments:
      - number: 11:21
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic and the Targum (Hebrew-Aramaic
          commentary).    '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "A beautiful woman who abandons good moralsis like a fine gold ring
        dangling from a pig\u2019s snout."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: True lovers of God are filled with longingsfor what is pleasing and
        good,but the wicked can only expect doom.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Generosity brings prosperity,but withholding from charity brings poverty.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Those who live to bless otherswill have blessings heaped upon them,and
        the one who pours out his life to pour out blessingswill be saturated with
        favor. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 11:25
        content: "  The Hebrew phrase here literally means \u201CThe soul of blessing
          will grow fat.\u201D    "
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: People will curse the businessman with no ethics,but the one with
        a social conscience receives praise from all. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 11:26
        content: "  The Hebrew phrase here literally means \u201CThe one who withholds
          produce will be cursed, but blessing will be on the head of the one who
          sells it.\u201D    "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Living your life seeking what is good for others brings untold favor,but
        those who wish evil for others will find it coming back on them.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Keep trusting in your riches and down you\u2019ll go!But the lovers
        of God rise up like flowers in the spring."
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: The fool who brings trouble to his own familywill be cut out of the
        will,and the family servant will do better than he.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: But a life lived loving God bears lasting fruit,for the one who is
        truly wise wins souls. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 11:30
        content: "  As translated from the Hebrew. The Aramaic and the Septuagint
          read \u201Cthe souls of violent ones will be removed.\u201D    "
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "If the righteous are barely saved,what\u2019s in store for all the
        wicked? [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 11:31
        content: '  As translated from the Septuagint. See  .  '
  - verses:
    - name: "1: It\u2019s Right to Live for God"
      title: "It\u2019s Right to Live for God"
      number: 1
      content: To learn the truth you must long to be teachable, [[COMMENT(0)]]or
        you can despise correction and remain ignorant.
      comments:
      - number: 12:1
        content: '  There are times when even the wise need correction, but they
          will appreciate its value.    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: If your heart is right, favor flows from the Lord,but a devious heart
        invites his condemnation.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You can\u2019t expect success by doing what\u2019s wrong.But the
        lives of his lovers are deeply rooted and firmly planted."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The integrity and strength of a virtuous wife [[COMMENT(0)]]transforms
        her husband into an honored king. But the wife who disgraces her husbandweakens
        the strength of his identity. '
      comments:
      - number: 12:4
        content: "  There is an amazing Hebrew word used here. It is more commonly
          used to describe warriors, champions, and mighty ones. Many translations
          read \u201Can excellent wife.\u201D But the meaning of the Hebrew word   
          is better translated \u201Can army that is wealthy,\u201D \u201Cstrong,\u201D
          \u201Cmighty,\u201D \u201Cpowerful,\u201D \u201Cwith substance,\u201D \u201Cvaliant,\u201D
          \u201Cvirtuous,\u201D or \u201Cworthy.\u201D      Or \u201CAn excellent
          wife is the crown of her husband.\u201D By implication, her dignity makes
          him a king.      Or \u201Cshe is like cancer in his bones.\u201D Bones
          are a metaphor for inner strength, our inner being, or identity.    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The lovers of God are filled with good ideasthat are noble and pure,but
        the schemes of the sinnerare crammed with nothing but lies.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: The wicked use their words to ambush and accuse, [[COMMENT(0)]]but
        the lovers of God speak to defend and protect.
      comments:
      - number: 12:6
        content: "  Or \u201Clie in wait for blood.\u201D This is a figure of speech
          for accusation.    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The wicked are taken out, gone for good,but the godly families shall
        live on.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Everyone admires a man of principles,but the one with a corrupt heart
        is despised.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Just be who you are and work hard for a living,for that\u2019s better
        than pretending to be importantand starving to death."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: A good man takes care of the needs of his pets,while even the kindest
        acts of a wicked man are still cruel.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Work hard at your job and you\u2019ll have what you need.Following
        a get-rich-quick scheme is nothing but a fantasy."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Wisdom Means Being Teachable'
      title: Wisdom Means Being Teachable
      number: 12
      content: 'The cravings of the wicked are only for what is evil, [[COMMENT(0)]]but
        righteousness is the core motivation for the lovers of God,and it keeps them
        content and flourishing. '
      comments:
      - number: 12:12
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint. The Hebrew is \u201CThieves
          crave the loot of other thieves.\u201D      The meaning of the Hebrew text
          of v.    is uncertain.    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: The wicked will get trapped by their wordsof gossip, slander, and
        lies. [[COMMENT(0)]]But for the righteous, honesty is its own defense.
      comments:
      - number: 12:13
        content: "  The Hebrew is simply \u201Csinful words,\u201D which implies
          gossip, slander, and lies.    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: For there is great satisfaction in speaking the truth,and hard work
        brings blessings back to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Learning to Speak Wisely'
      title: Learning to Speak Wisely
      number: 15
      content: A fool is in love with his own opinion,but wisdom means being teachable.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "If you shrug off an insult and refuse to take offense,you demonstrate
        discretion indeed. [[COMMENT(0)]]But the fool has a short fuseand will immediately
        let you know when he\u2019s offended."
      comments:
      - number: 12:16
        content: "  Or \u201CA shrewd man conceals his shame.\u201D    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Truthfulness marks the righteous,but the habitual liar can never be
        trusted.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Reckless words are like the thrusts of a sword,cutting remarks meant
        to stab and to hurt.But the words of the wise soothe and heal.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Truthful words will stand the test of time,but one day every lie will
        be seen for what it is.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Deception fills the hearts of those who plot harm,but those who plan
        for peace [[COMMENT(0)]] are filled with joy.
      comments:
      - number: 12:20
        content: "  Or \u201Ccounselors of peace.\u201D    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Calamity is not allowed to overwhelm the righteous,but there\u2019s
        nothing but trouble waiting for the wicked."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Live in the truth and keep your promises,and the Lord will keep delighting
        in you,but he detests a liar.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Those who possess wisdom don\u2019t feel the needto impress others
        with what they know,but foolish ones make sure their ignorance is on display."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "If you want to reign in life, [[COMMENT(0)]]don\u2019t sit on your
        hands.Instead, work hard at doing what\u2019s right,for the slacker will
        end up working to make someone else succeed."
      comments:
      - number: 12:24
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Creign\u201D () is the title of the
          book: Proverbs. See introduction and the footnote on  .    "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Anxious fear brings depression,but a life-giving word of encouragementcan
        do wonders to restore joy to the heart. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 12:25
        content: "  This insightful proverb can also be translated \u201CStop worrying!
          Think instead of what brings you gladness.\u201D Our focus must never be
          on what we can\u2019t change but on the everlasting joy we have in Christ.
          Sometimes we have to find the life-giving word of encouragement rising
          up in our own hearts. This is the secret of finding perpetual encouragement
          by the Word that lives in us.    "
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Lovers of God give good advice to their friends, [[COMMENT(0)]]but
        the counsel of the wicked will lead them astray.
      comments:
      - number: 12:26
        content: '  As translated from older Aramaic manuscripts. The Hebrew is uncertain.    '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "A passive person won\u2019t even complete a project,but a passionate
        person makes good useof his time, wealth, and energy. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 12:27
        content: "  Implied in the text, paraphrased from an uncertain Hebrew phrase.
          An alternate translation would be \u201CA lazy person won\u2019t get to
          roast the game he caught, but the wealth of a diligent person is precious.\u201D    "
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Abundant life is discovered by walking in righteousness,but holding
        on to your anger leads to death. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 12:28
        content: '  As translated from the Septuagint and the Aramaic. The Hebrew
          is uncertain.  '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Living Wisely'
      title: Living Wisely
      number: 1
      content: "A wise son or daughter desires a father\u2019s discipline,but the
        know-it-all never listens to correction."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: The words of the wise are kind and easy to swallow,but the unbeliever
        just wants to pick a fight and argue.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Guard your words and you\u2019ll guard your life,but if you don\u2019t
        control your tongue,it will ruin everything."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: The slacker wants it all and ends up with nothing,but the hard worker
        ends up with all that he longed for.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Lovers of God hate what is phony and false,but the wicked are full
        of shame and behave shamefully. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 13:5
        content: "  The Hebrew word used here literally means \u201Cto cause a stink\u201D
          or \u201Cto emit an odor.\u201D This is a figure of speech for what is
          shameful.    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Righteousness is like a shield of protection,guarding those who keep
        their integrity,but sin is the downfall of the wicked.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: One pretends to be rich but is poor.Another pretends to be poor but
        is quite rich. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 13:7
        content: "  It is never godly to be a phony. It\u2019s always better to be
          who you are and avoid pretense.    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The self-assurance of the rich is their money, [[COMMENT(0)]]but
        people don\u2019t kidnap and extort the poor!"
      comments:
      - number: 13:8
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201CThe salvation of the soul is a man\u2019s
          true wealth.\u201D    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The virtues of God\u2019s lovers shine brightly in the darkness,but
        the flickering lamp of the ungodly will be extinguished."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Wisdom opens your heart to receive wise counsel,but pride closes your
        ears to adviceand gives birth only to quarrels and strife.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Wealth quickly gained is quickly wasted [[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014easy
        come, easy go!But if you gradually gain wealth,you will watch it grow."
      comments:
      - number: 13:11
        content: "  Or \u201CWealth gained by fraud will dwindle.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "When hope\u2019s dream seems to drag on and on,the delay can be depressing.But
        when at last your dream comes true,life\u2019s sweetness will satisfy your
        soul. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 13:12
        content: "  Or \u201Cit is a tree of life.\u201D    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Despise the word, will you?Then you\u2019ll pay the price and it
        won\u2019t be pretty!But the one who honors the Father\u2019s holy instructionswill
        be rewarded."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: When the lovers of God teach you truth,a fountain of life opens up
        within you,and their wise instruction will deliver you from the ways of death.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Everyone admires a wise, sensible person,but the treacherous walk
        on the path of ruin. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 13:15
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic and the Septuagint. The Hebrew
          is uncertain.    '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Everything a wise and shrewd man doescomes from a source of revelation-knowledge,
        [[COMMENT(0)]]but the behavior of a fool puts foolishness on parade! '
      comments:
      - number: 13:16
        content: "  Or \u201CA wise person thinks ahead.\u201D      The implication
          is that the fool is unable to finish anything he begins.    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: An undependable messenger causes a lot of trouble,but the trustworthy
        and wise messengersrelease healing wherever they go. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 13:17
        content: "  God\u2019s sons and daughters are peacemakers, healers, and faithful
          deliverers for others.    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Poverty and disgrace come to the onewho refuses to hear criticism.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]But the one who is easy to correct is on the path of honor.
      comments:
      - number: 13:18
        content: "  As translated from the Hebrew. The Septuagint is \u201CInstruction
          removes poverty and disgrace.\u201D    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: When God fulfills your longings,sweetness fills your soul.But the
        wicked refuse to turn from darknessto see their desires come to pass. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 13:19
        content: '  Implied by the Hebrew parallelism of the text.    '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "If you want to grow in wisdom,spend time with the wise.Walk with
        the wickedand you\u2019ll eventually become just like them."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Calamity chases the sin-chaser,but prosperity pursues the God-lover.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The benevolent man leaves an inheritancethat endures to his children\u2019s
        children,but the wealth of the wicked is treasured up for the righteous."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: The lovers of God will live a long life and get to enjoy their wealth,but
        the ungodly will suddenly perish. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 13:23
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint. The Hebrew is \u201CIn the
          fallow ground of the poor there is abundance of food, but injustice sweeps
          it away.\u201D The Aramaic is \u201CThose who don\u2019t find the way of
          life destroy many years of wealth, and some are utterly destroyed.\u201D
          There is a vast difference in the three translations. This translation
          follows the Septuagint.    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'If you withhold correction and punishment [[COMMENT(0)]] from your
        children,you demonstrate a lack of true love.So prove your love and be prompt
        to punish them. '
      comments:
      - number: 13:24
        content: "  Or \u201Cspare the rod.\u201D Corporal punishment was common
          in premodern societies.      Or \u201CThe one who spares the rod hates
          his child.\u201D  "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: The lovers of God will have more than enough,but the wicked will always
        lack what they crave.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The House of Wisdom'
      title: The House of Wisdom
      number: 1
      content: Every wise woman encourages and builds up her family,but a foolish
        woman over time will tear it down by her own actions.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Lovers of truth follow the right pathbecause of their wonderment and
        worship of God.But the devious display their disdain for him.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The words of a proud fool will all come back to haunt him.But the
        words of the wisewill become a shield of protection around them.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The only clean stable is an empty stable.So if you want the work
        of an ox and to enjoy an abundant harvest,you\u2019ll have a mess or two
        to clean up!"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: An honest witness will never lie,but a deceitful witness lies with
        every breath.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The intellectually arrogant seek for wisdom,but they never seem to
        discoverwhat they claim they\u2019re looking for.For revelation-knowledge
        flows to the onewho hungers for understanding."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The words of the wise are like weapons of knowledge. [[COMMENT(0)]]If
        you need wise counsel, stay away from the fool.
      comments:
      - number: 14:7
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic.    '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: For the wisdom of the wise will keep life on the right track,while
        the fool only deceives himselfand refuses to face reality.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Fools mock the need for repentance, [[COMMENT(0)]]while the favor
        of God rests upon all his lovers.
      comments:
      - number: 14:9
        content: "  Or \u201CFools mock guilt [or guilt offering].\u201D The Septuagint
          is \u201CThe house of the transgressor owes purification.\u201D    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Don\u2019t expect anyone else to fully understandboth the bitterness
        and the joysof all you experience in your life."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The household of the wicked is soon torn apart,while the family of
        the righteous flourishes.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "You can rationalize it all you wantand justify the path of error
        you have chosen,but you\u2019ll find out in the end that you took the road
        to destruction."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Superficial laughter can hide a heavy heart,but when the laughter
        ends, the pain resurfaces.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Those who turn from the truth get what they deserve,but a good person
        receives a sweet reward. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 14:14
        content: "  As translated from Hebrew manuscripts. The Aramaic is \u201Ca
          good man will be filled from the awe of his soul.\u201D    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: A gullible person will believe anything,but a sensible person will
        confirm the facts.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: A wise person is careful in all things and turns quickly from evil,while
        the impetuous fool moves ahead with overconfidence.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: An impulsive person has a short fuse and can ruin everything,but the
        wise show self-control. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 14:17
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. The Hebrew is \u201Cand a crafty
          schemer is hated.\u201D The Greek Septuagint is \u201Ca sensible man bears
          up under many things.\u201D    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "The na\xEFve demonstrate a lack of wisdom,but the lovers of wisdom
        are crowned with revelation-knowledge."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Evil ones will pay tribute to good peopleand eventually come to be
        servants of the godly. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 14:19
        content: "  The Hebrew phrase literally means \u201Cthey will come [or bow]
          at the gates of the righteous.\u201D    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: The poor are disliked even by their neighbors,but everyone wants to
        get close to the wealthy.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "It\u2019s a sin to despise one who is less fortunate than you, [[COMMENT(0)]]but
        when you are kind to the poor,you will prosper and be blessed."
      comments:
      - number: 14:21
        content: "  Implied in the Hebrew parallelism. The Hebrew phrase here literally
          means \u201Cyour neighbor.\u201D    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Haven\u2019t you noticed how evil schemers always wander astray?But
        kindness and truth come to thosewho make plans to be pure in all their ways.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 14:22
        content: "  Both the Aramaic and the Septuagint insert a verse here that
          is not found in the Hebrew: \u201CThe followers of evil don\u2019t understand
          mercy and faith, but you\u2019ll find kindness and faith with those who
          do good.\u201D    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: If you work hard at what you do,great abundance will come to you.But
        merely talking about getting richwhile living to only pursue your pleasures
        [[COMMENT(0)]]brings you face-to-face with poverty. <smallcaps>  </smallcaps>
      comments:
      - number: 14:23
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint.      There is an additional
          verse found here in the Aramaic that is missing from the Hebrew text: \u201CThe
          Lord  heals every sickness, but evil speaking makes you sick [harms you].\u201D    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The true net worth of the wise [[COMMENT(0)]] is the wealth that
        wisdom imparts.But the way of life for the fool is his foolishness. '
      comments:
      - number: 14:24
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe crown of the wise.\u201D      The Aramaic word translated
          here as \u201Cfoolishness\u201D can also mean \u201Cinsanity.\u201D    "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Speak the truth and you\u2019ll save souls,but in the spreading of
        lies treachery thrives."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Confidence and strength flood the heartsof the lovers of God who live
        in awe of him,and their devotion provides their childrenwith a place of shelter
        and security. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 14:26
        content: '  To live as a passionate lover of God will bring benefit even
          to your children.    '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "To worship God in wonder and aweopens a fountain of life within you,empowering
        you to escape death\u2019s domain. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 14:27
        content: "  Or \u201Cempowering you to turn from the deadly snares.\u201D    "
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: A king glories in the number of his loyal followers,but a dwindling
        population spells ruin for any leader.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "When your heart overflows with understandingyou\u2019ll be very slow
        to get angry.But if you have a quick temper,your impatience will be quickly
        seen by all."
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: A tender, tranquil heart will make you healthy, [[COMMENT(0)]]but
        jealousy can make you sick.
      comments:
      - number: 14:30
        content: "  Or \u201CA heart of healing is the life of the flesh.\u201D    "
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Insult your Creator, will you?That\u2019s exactly what you doevery
        time you oppress the powerless! [[COMMENT(0)]]Showing kindness to the poor
        is equal to honoring your maker."
      comments:
      - number: 14:31
        content: "  Or \u201Cslander the poor.\u201D Every human being is made in
          God\u2019s image, including the poor.    "
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: The wicked are crushed by every calamity,but the righteous find a
        strong hopein the time of death. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 14:32
        content: "  As translated from the Masoretic Text. Our strong hope is that
          our lives will continue in the presence of God in the resurrection glory.
          Both the Septuagint and the Aramaic read quite differently: \u201Cbut the
          righteous have a refuge in their integrity.\u201D    "
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Wisdom soothes the heart of the one with living-understanding,but
        the heart of the fool just stockpiles stupidity.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: A nation is exalted by the righteousness of its people,but sin heaps
        disgrace upon the land.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: A wise and faithful servant receives promotion from the king,but the
        one who acts disgracefullygets to taste the anger of the king. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 14:35
        content: "  As translated from the Hebrew. The Septuagint reads \u201Cand
          by his good behavior shame is removed.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Wisdom Far Better than Wickedness'
      title: Wisdom Far Better than Wickedness
      number: 1
      content: "Respond gently when you are confrontedand you\u2019ll defuse the
        rage of another.Responding with sharp, cutting words [[COMMENT(0)]] will
        only make it worse.Don\u2019t you know that being angrycan ruin the testimony
        of even the wisest of men? "
      comments:
      - number: 15:1
        content: "  Or \u201Cpainful words.\u201D      This sentence is found only
          in the Septuagint.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: When wisdom speaks, understanding becomes attractive.But the words
        of the fool make their ignorance look laughable. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 15:2
        content: "  The Aramaic reads \u201CThe mouths of fools vomit a curse.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The eyes of the Lord [[COMMENT(0)]] are everywhereand he takes note
        of everything that happens.He watches over his lovers,and he also sees the
        wickedness of the wicked.
      comments:
      - number: 15:3
        content: "  \u201CThe eyes of the Lord\u201D can also be a metaphor for his
          prophets.    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: When you speak healing words,you offer others fruit from the tree
        of life.But unhealthy, negative words do nothing but crush their hopes. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 15:4
        content: "  Or \u201Cperverse words are the crushing of the spirit.\u201D    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "You\u2019re stupid to mock the instruction of a father,but welcoming
        correction will make you brilliant. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 15:5
        content: "  The Septuagint adds a verse that is not found in the Hebrew:
          \u201CIn great righteousness there is great strength. But the ungodly will
          one day perish from the earth.\u201D    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: There is prosperity in the house of the righteous, [[COMMENT(0)]]but
        the house of the wicked is filled with trouble,no matter how much money they
        have.
      comments:
      - number: 15:6
        content: "  The Septuagint and the Aramaic read \u201CThere is power in the
          house of the righteous.\u201D Both concepts are valid.    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: When wisdom speaks, revelation-knowledge is released, [[COMMENT(0)]]but
        finding true wisdom in the word of a fool is futile.
      comments:
      - number: 15:7
        content: "  Or \u201Cis scattered like seed.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: It is despicable to the Lordwhen people use the worship of the Almightyas
        a cloak for their sin, [[COMMENT(0)]]but every prayer of the righteous is
        pleasing to his heart.
      comments:
      - number: 15:8
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe sacrifice of the wicked\u201D; that is, worshiping
          God with a wicked heart, only to hide sin. Our yielded hearts must be the
          sacrifice we offer to God.    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: The Lord detests the lifestyle of the wicked,but he loves those who
        pursue purity. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 15:9
        content: "  The Aramaic reads \u201Che shows mercy to the one who practices
          righteousness.\u201D    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Severe punishment awaits the onewho turns away from the truth,and
        those who rebel against correction will die.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Even hell itself holds no secrets from the Lord God,for before his
        eyes, all is exposed\u2014and so much more the heart of every human being."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Living an Ascended Life'
      title: Living an Ascended Life
      number: 12
      content: The know-it-all never esteems the one who tries to correct him.He
        refuses to seek good advice from the wise. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 15:12
        content: "  Another way to say this is \u201CThe one who hates authority
          has no love for being taught.\u201D    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: A cheerful heart puts a smile on your face,but a broken heart leads
        to depression.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Lovers of God [[COMMENT(0)]] hunger after truth,but those without
        understandingfeast on foolishness and don\u2019t even realize it."
      comments:
      - number: 15:14
        content: "  Or \u201CThe upright\u201D (Aramaic).    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Everything seems to go wrongwhen you feel weak and depressed.But when
        you choose to be cheerful,every day will bring you more and more joy and
        fullness. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 15:15
        content: "  The Septuagint reads quite differently: \u201CAnd the good [heart]
          is always calm.\u201D    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "It\u2019s much better to live simply,surrounded in holy awe and worship
        of God,than to have great wealth with a home full of trouble."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "It\u2019s much better to have a meal of vegetables surrounded with
        love and gracethan a steak where there is hate."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: A touchy, hot-tempered man picks a fight,but the calm, patient man
        knows how to silence strife.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Nothing seems to work right [[COMMENT(0)]] for the lazy man,but life
        seems smooth and easy when your heart is virtuous.
      comments:
      - number: 15:19
        content: "  Or \u201CThe way is blocked with thorns.\u201D    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "When a son learns wisdom,a father\u2019s heart is glad.But the man
        who shames [[COMMENT(0)]] his mother is a foolish son."
      comments:
      - number: 15:20
        content: "  Or \u201Cdespises.\u201D    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: The senseless fool treats life like a joke,but the one with living-understanding
        makes good choices.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Your plans will fall apart right in front of youif you fail to get
        good advice.But if you first seek out multiple counselors,you\u2019ll watch
        your plans succeed."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Everyone enjoys giving great advice.But how delightful it is to say
        the right thing at the right time!
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: The life-paths of the prudent lift them progressively heavenward,delivering
        them from the death spiralsthat keep tugging them downward.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The Lord champions the widow\u2019s cause, [[COMMENT(0)]]but watch
        him as he smashes down the houses of the haughty!"
      comments:
      - number: 15:25
        content: "  Or \u201CThe Lord maintains the boundaries of the widow.\u201D    "
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: The Lord detests wicked ways of thinking, [[COMMENT(0)]]but he enjoys
        lovely and delightful words.
      comments:
      - number: 15:26
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe thoughts of the wicked.\u201D    "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: The one who puts earning money above his familywill have trouble at
        home,but those who refuse to exploit otherswill live in peace.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Lovers of God think before they speak,but the careless blurt out wicked
        words meant to cause harm.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "The Lord doesn\u2019t respond to the wicked,but he\u2019s moved to
        answer the prayers of the righteous."
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Eyes that focus on what is beautiful bring joy to the heart, [[COMMENT(0)]]and
        hearing a good reportrefreshes and strengthens the inner being. '
      comments:
      - number: 15:30
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint. The Hebrew is \u201CThe light
          of the eyes brings joy.\u201D      The Hebrew here literally means \u201Cmakes
          fat your bones.\u201D Bones picture our inner being.    "
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Accepting constructive criticismopens your heart to the path of life,making
        you right at home among the wise.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: Refusing constructive criticism showsyou have no interest in improving
        your life,for revelation-insight only comes as you accept correctionand the
        wisdom that it brings.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "The source of revelation-knowledge is foundas you fall down in surrender
        before the Lord.Don\u2019t expect to see Shekinah gloryuntil the Lord sees
        your sincere humility. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 15:33
        content: "  Or \u201CBefore honor is humility.\u201D The Hebrew uses the
          word  , which is translated as \u201Cglory\u201D 156 times in the Old Testament.  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Wisdom Exalts God'
      title: Wisdom Exalts God
      number: 1
      content: "Go ahead and make all the plans you want,but it\u2019s the Lord who
        will ultimately direct your steps. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 16:1
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint. The Hebrew and Aramaic read
          \u201Cthe Lord gives the right reply.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "We are all in love with our own opinions,convinced they\u2019re correct.But
        the Lord is in the midst of us, [[COMMENT(0)]]testing and probing our every
        motive."
      comments:
      - number: 16:2
        content: "  Or \u201Cin the midst of spirits.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Before you do anything,put your trust totally in God and not in yourself.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]Then every plan you make will succeed.
      comments:
      - number: 16:3
        content: "  Or \u201Ccommit your business to God.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The Lord works everything together to accomplish his purpose. [[COMMENT(0)]]Even
        the wicked are included in his plans\u2014he sets them aside for the day
        of disaster."
      comments:
      - number: 16:4
        content: "  Or \u201Cfor its answer.\u201D    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> detests all the proud [[COMMENT(0)]]
        of heart,for pride attracts his punishment\u2014and you can count on that!"
      comments:
      - number: 16:5
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Cproud\u201D is  , which comes from
          a root word that means \u201Clocust\u201D (as a reference to a locust swarm
          that devours all the crops). Pride is like a locust swarm that always hinders
          a true spiritual harvest within us.    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "You can avoid evil through surrendered worshipand the fear of God,for
        the power of his faithful loveremoves sin\u2019s guilt and grip over you."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When the Lord is pleased with the decisions you\u2019ve made,he activates
        grace to turn enemies into friends."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: It is better to have little with a heart that loves justicethan to
        be rich and not have God on your side.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Living like a King'
      title: Living like a King
      number: 9
      content: Within your heart you can make plans for your future,but the Lord
        chooses the steps you take to get there.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: A king speaks the revelation of truth,so he must be extraordinarily
        careful in the decrees that he makes.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The Lord expects you to be fair in every business deal,for he is the
        one who sets the standards for righteousness. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 16:11
        content: "  Or \u201CHonesty with scales and balances is the way of the Lord,
          for all the stones in the bag are established by him.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Kings and leaders despise wrongdoing,for the true authority to rule
        and reignis built on a foundation of righteousness.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Kings and leaders love to hear godly counsel,and they love those who
        tell them the truth.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: The anger of a king releases the messenger of death, [[COMMENT(0)]]but
        a wise person will know how to pacify his wrath.
      comments:
      - number: 16:14
        content: '  See  ,  ,  .    '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Life-giving light streams from the presence of a king, [[COMMENT(0)]]and
        his favor is showered upon those who please him.
      comments:
      - number: 16:15
        content: "  The Septuagint reads \u201CThe king\u2019s son is in the light
          of life.\u201D    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Everyone wants gold, but wisdom\u2019s worth [[COMMENT(0)]] is far
        greater.Silver is sought after,but a heart of understanding yields a greater
        return."
      comments:
      - number: 16:16
        content: "  The Septuagint is \u201Cnests of wisdom.\u201D    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Repenting from evil places you on the highway of holiness.Protect
        purity and you protect your life. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 16:17
        content: "  There are two proverbs inserted here in the Septuagint that are
          not found in the Hebrew or Aramaic: \u201CReceive instruction and you\u2019ll
          be prosperous; he who listens to correction shall be made wise.\u201D \u201CHe
          who guards his ways preserves his own soul; he who loves his life will
          watch his words.\u201D    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Your boast becomes a prophecy of a future failure.The higher you
        lift yourself up in pride, [[COMMENT(0)]]the harder you\u2019ll fall in disgrace."
      comments:
      - number: 16:18
        content: "  Or \u201Coverconfidence.\u201D    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "It\u2019s better to be meek and lowly and live among the poorthan
        to live high and mighty among the rich and famous."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Walking with Wisdom'
      title: Walking with Wisdom
      number: 20
      content: One skilled in business discovers prosperity,but the one who trusts
        in God is blessed beyond belief!
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The one with a wise heart is called \u201Cdiscerning,\u201Dand speaking
        sweetly to othersmakes your teaching even more convincing."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Wisdom is a deep well of understandingopened up within you as a fountain
        of life for others,but it\u2019s senseless to try to instruct a fool."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Winsome words pour from a heart of wisdom,adding value to all you
        teach.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Nothing is more appealingthan speaking beautiful, life-giving words.For
        they release sweetness to our soulsand inner healing to our spirits. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 16:24
        content: "  Or \u201Chealing to the bones.\u201D Bones are a metaphor for
          our inner being.    "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Before every person there is a paththat seems like the right one to
        take,but it leads straight to hell! [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 16:25
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint. The Hebrew is \u201Cthe ways
          of death.\u201D    "
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Life motivation comes from the deep longings of the heart,and the
        passion to see them fulfilled urges you onward. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 16:26
        content: '  The meaning of the Hebrew in this verse is uncertain.    '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: A wicked scoundrel wants to dig up dirt on others,only to spread slander
        and shred their reputation.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: A twisted person spreads rumors;a whispering gossip ruins good friendships.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: A vicious criminal can be persuasive,enticing others to join him as
        partners in crime,but he leads them all down a despicable path.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "It\u2019s easy to tell when a wicked manis hatching some crooked
        scheme\u2014it\u2019s written all over his face.His looks betray him as he
        gives birth to his sin."
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Old age with wisdom will crown you with dignity and honor, [[COMMENT(0)]]for
        it takes a lifetime of righteousness to acquire it.
      comments:
      - number: 16:31
        content: "  Or \u201CGray hair is a crown of splendor.\u201D In the Hebrew
          culture the old were honored above all, especially if they acquired wisdom.
          See  .    "
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Do you want to be a mighty warrior?It\u2019s better to be known as
        one who is patient and slow to anger. [[COMMENT(0)]]Do you want to conquer
        a city?Rule over your temper before you attempt to rule a city."
      comments:
      - number: 16:32
        content: "  The Septuagint is \u201CIt\u2019s better to be forgiving than
          strong.\u201D    "
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "We may toss the coin and roll the dice,but God\u2019s will is greater
        than luck. [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>  </smallcaps>"
      comments:
      - number: 16:33
        content: "  Or \u201CInto the center the lot is cast and from  is all its
          judgment.\u201D The casting of lots was a common form of divination in
          premodern societies.  "
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Wisdom\u2019s Virtues"
      title: "Wisdom\u2019s Virtues"
      number: 1
      content: A simple, humble life with peace and quietis far better than an opulent
        lifestyle with nothingbut quarrels and strife at home.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "A wise, intelligent servant will be honored above a shameful son.He\u2019ll
        even end up having a portion left to him in his master\u2019s will."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: In the same way that gold and silver are refined by fire,the Lord
        purifies your heart by the tests and trials of life.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Those eager to embrace evil listen to slander,for a liar loves to
        listen to lies.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Mock the poor, will you?You insult your Creator every time you do!If
        you make fun of others\u2019 misfortune,you\u2019d better watch out\u2014your
        punishment is on its way."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Grandparents have the crowning glory of life:grandchildren!And it\u2019s
        only proper for children to take pride in their parents. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 17:6
        content: "  Or \u201Cfathers.\u201D There is an additional verse found in
          the Septuagint that is inserted here: \u201CA whole world of riches belongs
          to the faithful, but the unfaithful don\u2019t get even a cent.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "It is not proper for a leader to lie and deceive,and don\u2019t expect
        excellent words to be spoken by a fool. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 17:7
        content: '  Two absurd things are to find a fool in leadership and to have
          a leader in foolishness.    '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Wise instruction [[COMMENT(0)]] is like a costly gem.It turns the
        impossible into success.
      comments:
      - number: 17:8
        content: "  \u201CInstruction\u201D is taken from the Aramaic and the Septuagint.
          The Hebrew reads \u201Cbribe.\u201D    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Love overlooks the mistakes of others,but dwelling on the failures
        of others devastates friendships.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: One word of correction breaks open a teachable heart,but a fool can
        be corrected a hundred timesand still not know what hit him.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Rebellion thrives in an evil man,so a messenger of vengeance [[COMMENT(0)]]
        will be sent to punish him. '
      comments:
      - number: 17:11
        content: "  Or \u201Cmerciless angels.\u201D      This could mean an evil
          spirit or calamities and sorrows.    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "It\u2019s safer to meet a grizzly bear robbed of her cubsthan to
        confront a reckless fool."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: The one who returns evil for goodcan expect to be treated the same
        way for the rest of his life. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 17:13
        content: "  Or \u201Cevil will haunt his house.\u201D    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Don\u2019t be one who is quick to quarrel,for an argument is hard
        to stop,and you never know how it will end,so don\u2019t even start down
        that road! [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 17:14
        content: "  The Aramaic for this verse reads \u201CTo shed blood provokes
          the judgment of a ruler.\u201D    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: There is nothing God hates morethan condemning the one who is innocentand
        acquitting the one who is guilty.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Why pay tuition to educate a fool?For he has no intention of acquiring
        true wisdom.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: A dear friend will love you no matter what,and a family sticks together
        through all kinds of trouble.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "It\u2019s stupid to run up bills you\u2019ll never be able to payor
        to cosign for the loan of your friend.Save yourself the trouble and don\u2019t
        do either one."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: If you love to argue,then you must be in love with sin.For the one
        who loves to boast [[COMMENT(0)]] is only asking for trouble.
      comments:
      - number: 17:19
        content: "  Or \u201Che who builds a high gate.\u201D The gate becomes a
          picture of the mouth. This is a figure of speech for proud boasting.    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: The one with a perverse heart never has anything good to say, [[COMMENT(0)]]and
        the chronic liar tumbles into constant trouble.
      comments:
      - number: 17:20
        content: "  Or \u201Ccan expect calamity.\u201D    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Parents of a numbskull will have many sorrows,for there\u2019s nothing
        about his lifestyle that will make them proud."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: A joyful, cheerful heart brings healing to both body and soul.But
        the one whose heart is crushedstruggles with sickness and depression.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: When you take a secret bribe,your actions reveal your true character,for
        you pervert the ways of justice.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Even the face of a wise man shows his intelligence.But the wandering
        eyes of a fool will look for wisdom everywhereexcept right in front of his
        nose.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: A father grieves over the foolishness of his child,and bitter sorrow
        fills his mother.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "It\u2019s horrible to persecute a holy lover of Godor to strike an
        honorable man for his integrity!"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Can you bridle your tongue when your heart is under pressure?That\u2019s
        how you show that you are wise.An understanding heart keeps you cool, calm,
        and collected,no matter what you\u2019re facing."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "When even a fool bites his tongue [[COMMENT(0)]]he\u2019s considered
        wise.So shut your mouth when you are provoked\u2014it will make you look
        smart."
      comments:
      - number: 17:28
        content: "  The Septuagint is \u201CWhen an unthinking man asks a question.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Wisdom Gives Life'
      title: Wisdom Gives Life
      number: 1
      content: An unfriendly person isolates himselfand seems to care only about
        his own issues.For his contempt of sound judgment makes him a recluse. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 18:1
        content: "  There are alternate possible translations of this verse in the
          Hebrew; for example, \u201CAn idle man meditates on his lusts and mocks
          wise instruction.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Senseless people find no pleasure in acquiring true wisdom,for all
        they want to do is impress you with what they know.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: An ungodly man is always cloaked with disgrace,as dishonor and shame
        are his companions.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Words of wisdom [[COMMENT(0)]] are like a fresh, flowing brook\u2014like
        deep waters that spring forth from within,bubbling up inside the one with
        understanding."
      comments:
      - number: 18:4
        content: "  Or \u201CWords that touch the heart.\u201D    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: It is atrocious when judges show favor to the guiltyand deprive the
        innocent of justice.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "A senseless man jumps headfirst into an argument;he\u2019s just asking
        for a beating for his reckless words. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 18:6
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201Chis rash words call for death.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "A fool has a big mouth that only gets him into trouble,and he\u2019ll
        pay the price for what he says."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The words of a gossip merely reveal the wounds of his own soul, [[COMMENT(0)]]and
        his slander penetrates into the innermost being.
      comments:
      - number: 18:8
        content: "  Scholars are somewhat uncertain about an exact translation of
          this phrase. The Aramaic is \u201CThe words of a lazy man lead him to fear
          and evil.\u201D    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: The one who is too lazy to look for workis the same one who wastes
        his life away.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The character of God is a tower of strength, [[COMMENT(0)]]for the
        lovers of God delight to run into his heartand be exalted on high.
      comments:
      - number: 18:10
        content: "  The Hebrew word  , translated as \u201Ctower of strength,\u201D
          has a homonym that can be translated \u201Cbed of flowers.\u201D    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The rich, in their conceit, imagine that their wealthis enough to
        protect them.It becomes their confidence in a day of trouble. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 18:11
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201CThe wealth of the rich is a strong city,
          and its glory casts a broad shadow.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "A man\u2019s heart is the proudest when his downfall is nearest,for
        he won\u2019t see glory until the Lord sees humility."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Listen before you speak,for to speak before you\u2019ve heard the
        facts will bring humiliation."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The will to live sustains you when you\u2019re sick, [[COMMENT(0)]]but
        depression crushes courage and leaves you unable to cope."
      comments:
      - number: 18:14
        content: "  The Septuagint is \u201CA wise servant can calm a man\u2019s
          anger.\u201D    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: The spiritually hungry are always ready to learn more,for their hearts
        are eager to discover new truths.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Would you like to meet a very important person?Take a generous gift.It
        will do wonders to gain entrance into his presence.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: There are two sides to every story.The first one to speak sounds true
        until you hear the other sideand they set the record straight. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 18:17
        content: '  The text implies that a legal testimony in a courtroom may seem
          to be correct until cross-examination begins.    '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: A coin toss [[COMMENT(0)]] resolves a disputeand can put an argument
        to restbetween formidable opponents.
      comments:
      - number: 18:18
        content: "  The Hebrew is \u201CCasting lots.\u201D    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "It is easier to conquer a strong citythan to win back a friend whom
        you\u2019ve offended.Their walls go up, making it nearly impossible to win
        them back. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 18:19
        content: "  Or \u201CA brother supported by a brother is like a high, strong
          city. They hold each other up like the bars of a fortress.\u201D    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Sharing words of wisdom is satisfying to your inner being.It encourages
        you to knowthat you\u2019ve changed someone else\u2019s life. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 18:20
        content: "  Or \u201CA man\u2019s belly is filled with the fruits of his
          mouth, and by the harvest of his lips he will be satisfied.\u201D    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Your words are so powerfulthat they will kill or give life,and the
        talkative person will reap the consequences.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'When a man finds a wife,he has found a treasure!For she is the gift
        of God to bring him joy and pleasure.But the one who divorces a good womanloses
        what is good from his house. [[COMMENT(0)]]To choose an adulteress is both
        stupid and ungodly. '
      comments:
      - number: 18:22
        content: '  The reference to divorce is not found in the Hebrew text but
          is included in both the Aramaic and the Septuagint.      As translated
          from the Septuagint.    '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: The poor plead for help from the rich,but all they get in return is
        a harsh response.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Some friendships don\u2019t last for long, [[COMMENT(0)]]but there
        is one loving friend who is joined to your heart closer than any other!"
      comments:
      - number: 18:24
        content: "  Or \u201CA man with too many friends may be broken to pieces.\u201D     
          The Hebrew word used here can be translated \u201Cjoined together,\u201D
          \u201Cstick close,\u201D \u201Cto cleave,\u201D \u201Cto pursue,\u201D
          or \u201Cto overtake.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Wisdom Exalted'
      title: Wisdom Exalted
      number: 1
      content: "It\u2019s better to be honest, even if it leads to poverty,than to
        live as a dishonest fool."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The best way to live is with revelation-knowledge,for without it,
        you\u2019ll grow impatient and run right into error. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 19:2
        content: "  Or \u201Csin.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: There are some people who ruin their own livesand then blame it all
        on God.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Being wealthy means having lots of \u201Cfriends,\u201Dbut the poor
        can\u2019t keep the ones they have."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Perjury won\u2019t go unpunished,and liars will get all that they
        deserve."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Everyone wants to be close to the rich and famous,but a generous person
        has all the friends he wants!
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When a man is poor, even his family has no use for him.How much more
        will his \u201Cfriends\u201D avoid him\u2014for though he begs for help,
        they won\u2019t respond. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 19:7
        content: "  The Aramaic and the Septuagint add a sentence not found in the
          Hebrew: \u201CThe one who is malicious with his words is not to be trusted.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Do yourself a favor and love wisdom.Learn all you can,then watch your
        life flourish and prosper!
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Tell lies and you\u2019re going to get caught,and the habitual liar
        is doomed."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "It doesn\u2019t seem right when you see a foolliving in the lap of
        luxuryor a prideful servant ruling over princes."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: An understanding person demonstrates patience,for mercy [[COMMENT(0)]]
        means holding your tongue.When you are insulted,be quick to forgive and forget
        it,for you are virtuous when you overlook an offense.
      comments:
      - number: 19:11
        content: "  The word translated \u201Cmercy\u201D (merciful) here is found
          only in the Septuagint.    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: The rage of a king is like the roar of a lion,but his sweet favor
        is like a gentle, refreshing rain.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "A rebellious son breaks a father\u2019s heart,and a nagging wife
        can drive you crazy!"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: You can inherit houses and land from your parents,but a good [[COMMENT(0)]]
        wife only comes as a gracious gift from God!
      comments:
      - number: 19:14
        content: "  Literally \u201Cprudent\u201D or \u201Cunderstanding\u201D wife.    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Go ahead\u2014be lazy and passive.But you\u2019ll go hungry if you
        live that way."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Honor God\u2019s holy instructionsand life will go well for you.But
        if you despise his ways and choose your own plans,you will die."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Every time you give to the poor you make a loan to the Lord.Don\u2019t
        worry\u2014you\u2019ll be repaid in full for all the good you\u2019ve done."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Don\u2019t be afraid to discipline your childrenwhile they\u2019re
        still young enough to learn.Don\u2019t indulge your children or be swayed
        by their protests."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "A hot-tempered man has to pay the price for his anger.If you bail
        him out once,you\u2019ll do it a dozen times. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 19:19
        content: "  There is an implication in the Hebrew that he will get into legal
          trouble. An alternate translation of this verse could be \u201CAn evil-minded
          man will be injured; if you rescue him, his anger will only intensify.\u201D    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Listen well to wise counseland be willing to learn from correctionso
        that by the end of your lifeyou\u2019ll be known for your wisdom."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "A person may have many ideas concerning God\u2019s plan for his life,but
        only the designs of God\u2019s purpose will succeed in the end."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: A man is charming when he displays tender mercies to others.And a
        lover of God who is poor and promises nothingis better than a rich liar who
        never keeps his promises.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "When you live a life of abandoned love,surrendered before the awe
        of God,here\u2019s what you\u2019ll experience:Abundant life. Continual protection.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]And complete satisfaction!"
      comments:
      - number: 19:23
        content: "  Or \u201CYou will not be remembered for evil.\u201D    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "There are some people who pretend they\u2019re hurt\u2014deadbeats
        who won\u2019t even work to feed themselves. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 19:24
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe lazy man buries his fork in his plate and won\u2019t
          even lift it to his mouth.\u201D    "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "If you punish the insolent who don\u2019t know any better,they will
        learn not to mock.But if you correct a wise man,he will grow even wiser."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Children who mistreat their parentsare an embarrassment to their family
        and a public disgrace.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "So listen, my child.Don\u2019t reject correctionor you will certainly
        wander from the ways of truth. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 19:27
        content: "  Or \u201CStop listening to instruction that contradicts what
          you know is truth.\u201D    "
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: A corrupt witness makes a mockery of justice,for the wicked never
        play by the rules. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 19:28
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe heart of the wicked feeds on evil.\u201D  "
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Judgment is waiting for those who mock the truth,and foolish living
        invites a beating.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Are You Living Wisely?'
      title: Are You Living Wisely?
      number: 1
      content: "A drunkard is obnoxious, loud, and argumentative;you\u2019re a fool
        to get intoxicated with strong drink."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: The rage of a king is like the roar of a lion.Do you really want to
        go and make him angry?
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: A person of honor [[COMMENT(0)]] will put an argument to rest.Only
        the stupid want to pick a fight.
      comments:
      - number: 20:3
        content: "  Or \u201CIt is the glory of a man.\u201D It\u2019s better to
          keep a friend than to win a fight.    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "If you\u2019re too lazy to plant seed,it\u2019s too bad when you
        have no harvest on which to feed. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 20:4
        content: "  The Aramaic and the Septuagint read \u201CRebuke a lazy man and
          he still has no shame, yet watch him go beg at harvest time.\u201D    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: A man of deep understanding will give good advice,drawing it out from
        the well within.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Many will tell you they\u2019re your loyal friends,but who can find
        one who is truly trustworthy? [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 20:6
        content: "  Or \u201CA compassionate man is hard to find, but it\u2019s even
          harder to find one who is faithful.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The lovers of God will walk in integrity,and their children are fortunateto
        have godly parents as their examples.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: A righteous king sits on his judgment seat.He scatters evil away from
        his kingdomby his wise discernment.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Which one of us can truly say,\u201CI am free from sin in my life,for
        my heart is clean and pure\u201D? [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 20:9
        content: "  The Hebrew word translated \u201Cclean\u201D can also mean \u201Cperfect\u201D
          or \u201Choly.\u201D The word translated \u201Cpure\u201D can also mean
          \u201Cclear,\u201D \u201Cbright,\u201D \u201Cshining,\u201D or \u201Cunmixed.\u201D
          Through God\u2019s grace, by the blood of Jesus, believers have been purified,
          made holy, and set free from our sins.    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Mark it down:God hates it when you demonstrate a double standard\u2014one
        for \u201Cthem\u201D and one for \u201Cyou.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "All children show what they\u2019re really like by how they act.You
        can discern their character,whether they are pure or perverse."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Lovers of God have been given eyes to seeand ears to hear from God.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "If you spend all your time sleeping, you\u2019ll grow poor.So wake
        up, sleepyhead! Don\u2019t sleep on the job.And then there will be plenty
        of food on your table."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The buyer says, as he haggles over the price,\u201CThat\u2019s junk.
        It\u2019s worthless!\u201DThen he goes out and brags,\u201CLook at the great
        bargain I got!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: You may have an abundance of wealth,piles of gold and jewels,but there
        is something of far greater worth:speaking revelation-words of knowledge.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Anyone stupid enough to guarantee a loan for a stranger [[COMMENT(0)]]deserves
        to have his property held as security.
      comments:
      - number: 20:16
        content: "  Some manuscripts have \u201Ca promiscuous woman.\u201D    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "What you obtain dishonestly may seem sweet at first,but sooner or
        later you\u2019ll live to regret it. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 20:17
        content: "  Or \u201CThe bread of falsehood may taste sweet at first, but
          afterward you\u2019ll have a mouth full of gravel.\u201D    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "If you solicit good advice, then your plans will succeed.So don\u2019t
        charge into battle without wisdom,for wars are won by skillful strategy."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "A blabbermouth will reveal your secrets,so stay away from people
        who can\u2019t keep their mouths shut. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 20:19
        content: "  The Aramaic adds a line: \u201COne who is faithful in spirit
          hides a matter.\u201D    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: If you despise your father or mother,your life will flicker out like
        a lamp,extinguished into the deepest darkness.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: If an inheritance is gained too early in life,it will not be blessed
        in the end.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Don\u2019t ever say, \u201CI\u2019m going to get even with themif
        it\u2019s the last thing I do!\u201DWrap God\u2019s grace around your heartand
        he will be the one to vindicate you."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The Lord hates double standards\u2014that\u2019s hypocrisy at its
        worst! [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 20:23
        content: "  Or \u201CThe Lord hates differing weights, and dishonest scales
          are wicked.\u201D    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: It is the Lord who directs your life,for each step you take is ordained
        by Godto bring you closer to your destiny.So much of your life, then, remains
        a mystery! [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 20:24
        content: "  The Aramaic reads \u201CSo what man is capable of ordering his
          way?\u201D    "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Be careful in making a rash promise before God,or you may be trapped
        by your vow and live to regret it.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: A wise king is able to discern corruptionand remove wickedness from
        his kingdom. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 20:26
        content: "  Or \u201CA wise king winnows the wicked and turns his chariot
          wheel over them.\u201D    "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: The spirit God breathed into man [[COMMENT(0)]] is like a living lamp,a
        shining lightsearching into the innermost chamber of our being.
      comments:
      - number: 20:27
        content: '  Implied by the Hebrew word  , also used in  .    '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Good leadership [[COMMENT(0)]] is built on love and truth,for kindness
        and integrityare what keep leaders in their position of trust.
      comments:
      - number: 20:28
        content: "  Or \u201CA king\u2019s throne.\u201D    "
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: We admire the young for their strength and beauty,but the dignity
        of the old is their wisdom. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 20:29
        content: "  Or \u201Ctheir gray hair.\u201D  "
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "When you are punished severely, you learn your lesson well\u2014for
        painful experiences do wonders to change your life."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Is the Source of Wisdom'
      title: God Is the Source of Wisdom
      number: 1
      content: "It\u2019s as easy for God to steer a king\u2019s heart [[COMMENT(0)]]
        for his purposesas it is for him to direct the course of a stream. "
      comments:
      - number: 21:1
        content: "  Don\u2019t forget, we have been made kings and priests by the
          blood of the Lamb. See  ;  ;  .      Because a leader\u2019s decisions
          affect so many people, God will intervene and steer them as a farmer steers
          the course of a stream to irrigate his fields.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "We may think we\u2019re right all the time,but God thoroughly examines
        our motives."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: It pleases God more when we demonstrate godliness and justicethan
        when we merely offer him a sacrifice.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Arrogance, superiority, and pride are the fruits of sin. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 21:4
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe tillage of the wicked.\u201D The Aramaic and the
          Septuagint have \u201Cthe lamp of the wicked.\u201D    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Brilliant ideas pay off and bring you prosperity,but making hasty,
        impatient decisionswill only lead to financial loss. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 21:5
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201CThe thoughts of the chosen one are trusting,
          but those of the evil one lead to poverty.\u201D This verse is missing
          from the Septuagint.    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: You can make a fortune dishonestly,but your crime will hold you in
        the snares of death! [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 21:6
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic and the Septuagint. The Hebrew
          is \u201Cthe money will vanish into thin air.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Violent rebels don\u2019t have a chance,for their rejection of truth
        and their love of evilwill drag them deeper into darkness."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: You can discern that a person is guilty by his devious actionsand
        the innocence of a person by his honest, sincere ways.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "It\u2019s better to live all alone in a rickety shackthan to share
        a castle with a crabby spouse! [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 21:9
        content: "  The Septuagint reads \u201CIt\u2019s better to live in the corner
          of an attic than in a large home plastered with unrighteousness.\u201D    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The wicked always crave what is evil;they\u2019ll show no mercy and
        get no mercy. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 21:10
        content: "  The Hebrew is \u201Cthey show no mercy,\u201D while the Septuagint
          reads \u201Cthey\u2019ll receive no mercy.\u201D This translation merges
          both concepts.    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Senseless people learn their lessons the hard way,but the wise are
        teachable.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'A godly, righteous person [[COMMENT(0)]] has the abilityto bring
        the light of instruction to the wickedeven though he despises what the wicked
        do. '
      comments:
      - number: 21:12
        content: "  The Hebrew is \u201Ca righteous one,\u201D which can also speak
          of God, \u201Cthe Righteous One.\u201D      As translated from the Septuagint.
          There are many examples of this in the Bible: Joseph in Egypt, Daniel in
          Babylon, and the follower of Jesus today who is living among unbelievers.    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "If you close your heart to the cries of the poor,then I\u2019ll close
        my ears when you cry out to me!"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Try giving a secret gift to the one who is angry with youand watch
        his anger disappear.A kind, generous gift goes a long wayto soothe the anger
        of one who is livid. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 21:14
        content: "  The Aramaic and Septuagint translate this \u201CHe who withholds
          a gift arouses anger.\u201D    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: When justice is served,the lovers of God celebrate and rejoice,but
        the wicked begin to panic.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: When you forsake the ways of wisdom,you will wander into the realm
        of dark spirits. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 21:16
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe congregation of the Rephaites.\u201D The Rephaites
          were a pagan tribe of giants and have been equated with spirits of darkness.
          See    and  .    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "To love pleasure for pleasure\u2019s sakewill introduce you to poverty.Indulging
        in a life of luxury [[COMMENT(0)]]will never make you wealthy."
      comments:
      - number: 21:17
        content: "  Or \u201Cloving wine and oil.\u201D    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: The wicked bring on themselvesthe very suffering they planned for
        others,for their treachery comes back to haunt them. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 21:18
        content: "  Or \u201CThe evil become the ransom payment for the righteous
          and the faithless for the upright.\u201D    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "It\u2019s better to live in a hut in the wildernessthan with a crabby,
        scolding spouse!"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "In wisdom\u2019s house you\u2019ll find delightful treasuresand the
        oil of the Holy Spirit. [[COMMENT(0)]]But the stupid  squander what they\u2019ve
        been given."
      comments:
      - number: 21:20
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Coil\u201D is an emblem of the Holy
          Spirit.      Or \u201Ca fool of a man.\u201D    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: The lovers of God who chase after righteousnesswill find all their
        dreams come true:an abundant life drenched with favorand a fountain that
        overflows with satisfaction. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 21:21
        content: "  Or \u201Crighteousness.\u201D    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: A warrior filled with wisdom ascends into the high placeand releases
        breakthrough,bringing down the strongholds of the mighty. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 21:22
        content: "  Or \u201Cdemolishing their strength of confidence.\u201D    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Watch your words and be careful what you say,and you\u2019ll be surprised
        by how few troubles you\u2019ll have."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "An arrogant man is inflated with pride\u2014nothing but a snooty
        scoffer in love with his own opinion.Mr. Mocker is his name! [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 21:24
        content: "  The Septuagint adds a line: \u201CHe who holds a grudge is a
          sinner.\u201D    "
    - name: '25-26: '
      title: 
      number: 25-26
      content: "Taking the easy way out is the habit of a lazy man,and it will be
        his downfall.All day long he thinks about all the things that he craves,for
        he hasn\u2019t learned the secret that the generous man has learned:extravagant
        giving never leads to poverty. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: "21:25\u201326"
        content: "  This is implied in the context and is necessary to complete the
          meaning of the proverb. The last line of this verse in the Septuagint reads
          \u201Cthe righteous lavish on others mercy and compassion.\u201D    "
    - name: '25-26: '
      title: 
      number: 25-26
      content: "Taking the easy way out is the habit of a lazy man,and it will be
        his downfall.All day long he thinks about all the things that he craves,for
        he hasn\u2019t learned the secret that the generous man has learned:extravagant
        giving never leads to poverty. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: "21:25\u201326"
        content: "  This is implied in the context and is necessary to complete the
          meaning of the proverb. The last line of this verse in the Septuagint reads
          \u201Cthe righteous lavish on others mercy and compassion.\u201D    "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: To bring an offering to God with an ulterior motive is detestable,for
        it amounts to nothing but hypocrisy.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: No one believes a notorious liar,but the guarded words of an honest
        man stand the test of time.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: The wicked are shameless and stubborn,but the lovers of God have a
        holy confidence.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: All your brilliant wisdom and clever insightwill be of no help at
        all if the Lord is against you.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: You can do your best to prepare for the battle, [[COMMENT(0)]]but
        ultimate victory comes from the Lord God.
      comments:
      - number: 21:31
        content: "  Or \u201CThe horse is prepared for the battle.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: How to Live a Life of Wisdom'
      title: How to Live a Life of Wisdom
      number: 1
      content: 'A beautiful reputation is more to be desired than great riches, [[COMMENT(0)]]and
        to be esteemed by others is more honorablethan to own immense investments. '
      comments:
      - number: 22:1
        content: "  The Hebrew is simply \u201Cname preferred to wealth.\u201D The
          Aramaic indicates it could be \u201Cthe name [of God].\u201D      Or \u201Csilver
          and gold.\u201D Remember, it is Solomon, one of the richest men to ever
          live, who penned these words.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: The rich and the poor have one thing in common:the Lord God created
        each one.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: A prudent person with insight foresees danger comingand prepares himself
        for it. [[COMMENT(0)]]But the senseless rush blindly forwardand suffer the
        consequences.
      comments:
      - number: 22:3
        content: '  Wise people solve problems before they happen.    '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Laying your life down in tender surrender before the Lordwill bring
        life, prosperity, and honor as your reward.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Twisted and perverse lives are surrounded by demonic influence. [[COMMENT(0)]]If
        you value your soul, stay far away from them.
      comments:
      - number: 22:5
        content: "  Or \u201Cthorns and snares.\u201D This becomes a metaphor for
          demonic curses and troubles. Thorns are associated with the fall of Adam.
          Jesus wore a crown of thorns and took away our curse. The snares picture
          the temptations of evil that the devil places in our path.    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Dedicate your children to Godand point them in the way that they
        should go, [[COMMENT(0)]]and the values they\u2019ve learned from you will
        be with them for life."
      comments:
      - number: 22:6
        content: "  Or \u201Ctrain them in the direction they are best suited to
          go.\u201D Some Jewish scholars teach this means understanding your children\u2019s
          talents and then seeing that they go into that field.    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "If you borrow money with interest,you\u2019ll end up serving the
        interests of your creditors, [[COMMENT(0)]]for the rich rule over the poor."
      comments:
      - number: 22:7
        content: "  The Septuagint reads \u201Cthe servant will lend to his own master.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Sin is a seed that brings a harvest;you\u2019ll reap a heap of trouble
        with every seed you plant.For your investment in sins pays a full return\u2014the
        full punishment you deserve! [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 22:8
        content: '  As translated from the Septuagint.    '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: When you are generous [[COMMENT(0)]] to the poor,you are enriched
        with blessings in return.
      comments:
      - number: 22:9
        content: "  The Hebrew word translated here as \u201Cgenerous\u201D actually
          means \u201Cto have a bountiful eye.\u201D It is a figure of speech for
          generosity, a life of helping others.    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Say goodbye to a troublemaker and you\u2019ll say goodbyeto quarrels,
        strife, tension, and arguments,for a troublemaker traffics in shame. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 22:10
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic.    '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The Lord loves those whose hearts are holy,and he is the friend of
        those whose ways are pure. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 22:11
        content: '  As translated from the Septuagint. Followers of Jesus enjoy a
          relationship with our holy King as we live in the light and love to please
          him.    '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: God passionately watches [[COMMENT(0)]] overhis deep reservoir  of
        revelation-knowledge,but he subverts the lies of those who pervert the truth.
      comments:
      - number: 22:12
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe eyes of the Lord [watch].\u201D In the church today,
          prophets become eyes in the body of Christ. They see and reveal God\u2019s
          heart for his people.      Although the concept of a reservoir is not found
          in the Hebrew, this translation adds it for poetic nuance.    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "A slacker always has an excuse for not working\u2014like \u201CI
        can\u2019t go to work. There\u2019s a lion outside!And murderers too!\u201D
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 22:13
        content: "  This humorous verse uses both satire and a metaphor. There\u2019s
          always an excuse for not working hard. The Aramaic text adds \u201CAnd
          murderers too!\u201D    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Sex with an adulteress is like falling into the abyss.Those under
        God\u2019s curse jump right in to their own destruction."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Although rebellion [[COMMENT(0)]] is woven into a young man\u2019s
        heart,tough discipline can make him into a man."
      comments:
      - number: 22:15
        content: "  The Aramaic word used here means \u201Csenseless.\u201D    "
    - name: '16: Sayings of the Wise Sages'
      title: Sayings of the Wise Sages
      number: 16
      content: There are two kinds of people headed toward poverty:those who exploit
        the poorand those who bribe the rich. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 22:16
        content: "  The Hebrew is literally \u201COppressing the poor is gain; giving
          to the rich is loss. Both end up only in poverty.\u201D    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Listen carefully and open your heart. [[COMMENT(0)]]Drink in the wise
        revelation that I impart.
      comments:
      - number: 22:17
        content: '  From this verse to    we have a collection of proverbs that lead
          to virtue. They are especially designed for the young person about to enter
          a career and start a family.    '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "You\u2019ll become winsome and wisewhen you treasure the beauty of
        my words.And always be prepared to share them at the appropriate time."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "For I\u2019m releasing these words to you this day,yes, even to you,
        so that your living hopewill be found in God alone,for he is the only one
        who is always true."
      comments: []
    - name: '20-21: '
      title: 
      number: 20-21
      content: Pay attention to these excellent sayings of three-fold things. [[COMMENT(0)]]For
        within my words you will discover true and reliable revelation.They will
        give you serenity  so that you can revealthe truth of the word of the one
        who sends you.
      comments:
      - number: "22:20\u201321"
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. Most translators find this verse
          difficult to convey. The Hebrew can be \u201CI have written excellent things,\u201D
          \u201CI have written three times,\u201D \u201CI write thirty sayings [proverbs],\u201D
          \u201CI have written you previously,\u201D or \u201CI have written you
          generals.\u201D The Septuagint reads \u201CYou should copy these things
          three times.\u201D If the Proverbs contain keys to understanding riddles
          and mysteries (see  ), then we have one of those keys given to us here.
          God speaks in threes, for he is a triune God. We have a body, soul, and
          spirit. God lived in a three-room house (the outer court, the Holy Place,
          and the chamber of the Most Holy Place). These three-fold dimensions are
          throughout the Bible.        is only found in the Aramaic.    "
    - name: '20-21: '
      title: 
      number: 20-21
      content: Pay attention to these excellent sayings of three-fold things. [[COMMENT(0)]]For
        within my words you will discover true and reliable revelation.They will
        give you serenity  so that you can revealthe truth of the word of the one
        who sends you.
      comments:
      - number: "22:20\u201321"
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. Most translators find this verse
          difficult to convey. The Hebrew can be \u201CI have written excellent things,\u201D
          \u201CI have written three times,\u201D \u201CI write thirty sayings [proverbs],\u201D
          \u201CI have written you previously,\u201D or \u201CI have written you
          generals.\u201D The Septuagint reads \u201CYou should copy these things
          three times.\u201D If the Proverbs contain keys to understanding riddles
          and mysteries (see  ), then we have one of those keys given to us here.
          God speaks in threes, for he is a triune God. We have a body, soul, and
          spirit. God lived in a three-room house (the outer court, the Holy Place,
          and the chamber of the Most Holy Place). These three-fold dimensions are
          throughout the Bible.        is only found in the Aramaic.    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Never oppress the pooror pass laws with the motive of crushing the
        weak.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: For the Lord will rise to plead their caseand humiliate the one who
        humiliates the poor. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 22:23
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. The Hebrew is \u201Che will rob
          the soul of the one who robs the poor.\u201D    "
    - name: '24-25: '
      title: 
      number: 24-25
      content: "Walk away from an angry manor you\u2019ll embrace a snare in your
        soul [[COMMENT(0)]]by becoming bad-tempered just like him."
      comments:
      - number: "22:24\u201325"
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic.    '
    - name: '24-25: '
      title: 
      number: 24-25
      content: "Walk away from an angry manor you\u2019ll embrace a snare in your
        soul [[COMMENT(0)]]by becoming bad-tempered just like him."
      comments:
      - number: "22:24\u201325"
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic.    '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Why would you ever guarantee a loan for someone elseor promise to
        be responsible for someone\u2019s debts?"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: For if you fail to pay you could lose your shirt! [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 22:27
        content: "  Or \u201Cbed.\u201D    "
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "The previous generation has set boundaries in place.Don\u2019t you
        dare move them just to benefit yourself. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 22:28
        content: "  This refers to moving property lines of your neighbors to take
          more land, or it could mean moving landmarks and memorials placed there
          by ancestors. It also speaks to the moral boundaries that the previous
          generation modeled\u2014they are to be upheld.  "
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "If you are uniquely gifted in your work,you will rise and be promoted.You
        won\u2019t be held back\u2014you\u2019ll stand before kings!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Wisdom Will Protect You'
      title: Wisdom Will Protect You
      number: 1
      content: "When you\u2019ve been invited to dine with a very important leader,consider
        your manners and keep in mind whom you\u2019re with."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Be careful to curb your appetite and catch yourselfbefore you fall
        into the trap of wanting all you see. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 23:2
        content: "  Or \u201Cput a knife to your throat.\u201D When you spend time
          with an important person, think about his needs, not your own, and favor
          will come on your life.    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Don\u2019t crave their delicacies,for they may have another motive
        in having you sit at their table."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Don\u2019t compare yourself to the rich. [[COMMENT(0)]]Surrender
        your selfish ambition and evaluate them properly."
      comments:
      - number: 23:4
        content: '  As translated from the Septuagint.    '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For no sooner do you start counting your wealththan it sprouts wings
        and flies away like an eagle in the sky\u2014here today, gone tomorrow!"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Be sensible when you dine with a stingy man [[COMMENT(0)]]and don\u2019t
        eat more than you should. "
      comments:
      - number: 23:6
        content: "  The Hebrew here literally means \u201Can evil eye,\u201D which
          is a metaphor for a stingy man.      Or \u201Cdon\u2019t crave his delicacies.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "For as he thinks within himself, so is he. [[COMMENT(0)]]He will
        grudgingly say, \u201CGo ahead and eat all you want,\u201Dbut in his heart
        he resents the fact that he has to pay for your meal."
      comments:
      - number: 23:7
        content: "  The Aramaic, the Septuagint, and a few Hebrew manuscripts read
          \u201CEating with him is like eating with someone with a hair in his throat\u2014his
          mind is not with you!\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "You\u2019ll be sorry you ate anything at all, [[COMMENT(0)]]and all
        your compliments will be wasted."
      comments:
      - number: 23:8
        content: "  Or \u201CYou\u2019ll vomit up the little you\u2019ve eaten.\u201D    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "A rebellious fool will despise your wise advice,so don\u2019t even
        waste your time\u2014save your breath!"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Never move a long-standing boundary lineor attempt to take land that
        belongs to the fatherless.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: For they have a mighty protector,a loving redeemer, [[COMMENT(0)]]
        who watches over them,and he will stand up for their cause.
      comments:
      - number: 23:11
        content: "  The Hebrew word here is  , which means \u201Ckinsman-redeemer.\u201D
          The Aramaic word means \u201CSavior.\u201D This shows powerfully how God
          will take up the grievances of the oppressed.    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Pay close attention to the teaching that corrects you,and open your
        heart to every word of instruction.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Don\u2019t withhold appropriate discipline from your child.Go ahead
        and punish him when he needs it. [[COMMENT(0)]]Don\u2019t worry\u2014it won\u2019t
        kill him!"
      comments:
      - number: 23:13
        content: "  The Hebrew is \u201Cstrike them with the rod.\u201D    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: A good spanking could be the very thingthat teaches him a lifelong
        lesson! [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 23:14
        content: "  Or \u201Crescues him from death.\u201D The Hebrew word is  .    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: My beloved child, when your heart is full of wisdom,my heart is full
        of gladness.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And when you speak anointed words, [[COMMENT(0)]]we are speaking
        mouth to mouth! '
      comments:
      - number: 23:16
        content: "  Or \u201Cspeak what is right.\u201D      This is taken from the
          Septuagint, and it literally means \u201CYour lips shall speak with my
          lips.\u201D The Hebrew is \u201CMy kidneys [soul] will rejoice.\u201D See 
          , which reveals that God spoke with Moses \u201Cmouth to mouth\u201D (literal
          Hebrew).    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Don\u2019t allow the actions of evil mento cause you to burn with
        anger. [[COMMENT(0)]]Instead, burn with unrelenting passionas you worship
        God in holy awe."
      comments:
      - number: 23:17
        content: "  The Hebrew word used here describes an emotion of intense passion.
          Many translate it \u201Cenvy\u201D (\u201CDo not envy the sinner\u201D),
          but that does not describe it fully. Another possible translation would
          be \u201Czeal.\u201D    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Your future is bright and filled with a living hopethat will never
        fade away.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: As you listen to me, my beloved child,you will grow in wisdom and
        your heartwill be drawn into understanding,which will empower you to make
        right decisions. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 23:19
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201Cset up my doctrines in your heart.\u201D    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Don\u2019t live in the excesses of drunkenness or gluttony,or waste
        your life away by partying all the time, [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 23:20
        content: '  Translated from the Aramaic and the Septuagint.    '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: because drunkards and gluttons sleep their lives awayand end up broke!
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Give respect to your father and mother,for without them you wouldn\u2019t
        even be here.And don\u2019t neglect them when they grow old."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Embrace the truth [[COMMENT(0)]] and hold it close.Don\u2019t let
        go of wisdom, instruction, and life-giving understanding."
      comments:
      - number: 23:23
        content: "  The Hebrew word here literally means \u201Ccreate the truth\u201D
          or \u201Cgive birth to truth\u201D or \u201Cpossess the truth.\u201D This
          Hebrew word is also used for God as the Creator. See  ,  .    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "When a father observes his child living in godliness,he is ecstatic
        with joy\u2014nothing makes him prouder!"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So may your father\u2019s heart burst with joyand your mother\u2019s
        soul be filled with gladness because of you."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "My son, give me your heartand embrace fully what I\u2019m about to
        tell you."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Stay far away from prostitutesand you\u2019ll stay far away from
        the pit of destruction.For sleeping with a promiscuous woman is like falling
        into a trapthat you\u2019ll never be able to escape!"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Like a robber hiding in the shadowsshe\u2019s waiting to claim another
        victim\u2014another husband unfaithful to his wife."
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Who has anguish? Who has bitter sorrow?Who constantly complains and
        argues?Who stumbles and falls and hurts himself?Who\u2019s the one with bloodshot
        eyes?"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "It\u2019s the one who drinks too muchand is always looking for a
        brew.Make sure it\u2019s never you!"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And don\u2019t be drunk with wine [[COMMENT(0)]]but be known as one
        who enjoys the companyof the lovers of God, "
      comments:
      - number: 23:31
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint.      As translated from the
          Septuagint and a marginal reading of the Hebrew. The Aramaic is \u201CMeditate
          on righteousness.\u201D The Septuagint adds a line not found in Hebrew
          or Aramaic that describes the unflattering life of a drunk: \u201CYou will
          walk around naked as a pestle!\u201D    "
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: for drunkenness brings the sting of a serpent,like the fangs of a
        viper [[COMMENT(0)]] spreading poison into your soul.
      comments:
      - number: 23:32
        content: "  Or \u201Chorned serpent\u201D or \u201Cdragon.\u201D This is
          an emblem of the poison of demonic power that can cause addictions and
          rule over the soul.  "
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: It will make you hallucinate, mumble,and speak words that are perverse.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "You\u2019ll be like a seasick sailor being tossed to and fro,dizzy
        and out of your mind."
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "You\u2019ll awake only to say, \u201CWhat hit me?I feel like I\u2019ve
        been run over by a truck!\u201DYet off you\u2019ll go, looking for another
        drink!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Wisdom\u2019s Warning"
      title: "Wisdom\u2019s Warning"
      number: 1
      content: "Don\u2019t envy the wealth of the wicked or crave their company."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "For they\u2019re obsessed with causing troubleand their conversations
        are corrupt."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Wise people are builders [[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014they build families,
        businesses, communities.And through intelligence and insighttheir enterprises
        are established and endure."
      comments:
      - number: 24:3
        content: "  Or \u201CA house is built by wisdom.\u201D The house is more
          than a structure with roof and a floor. It becomes a metaphor for families,
          churches, businesses, and enterprises.    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Because of their skilled leadership,the hearts [[COMMENT(0)]] of people
        are filled with the treasures of wisdomand the pleasures of spiritual wealth.
      comments:
      - number: 24:4
        content: "  Or \u201Cinner chambers.\u201D    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Wisdom can make anyone into a mighty warrior, [[COMMENT(0)]]and revelation-knowledge
        increases strength.
      comments:
      - number: 24:5
        content: "  Or \u201CWisdom makes anyone into a hero.\u201D The Aramaic and
          the Septuagint read \u201CIt\u2019s better to be wise than to be strong.\u201D    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Wise strategy is necessary to wage war,and with many astute advisersyou\u2019ll
        see the path to victory more clearly."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Wisdom is a treasure too lofty for a quarreling fool [[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014he\u2019ll
        have nothing to say when leaders gather together."
      comments:
      - number: 24:7
        content: "  The Hebrew is actually \u201CWisdom is coral to a fool.\u201D
          That is, it is unattainable, deep, and hidden.    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "There is one who makes plans to do evil\u2014Master Schemer is his
        name."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "If you plan to do evil, it\u2019s as wrong as doing it.And everyone
        detests a troublemaker."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: If you faint when under pressure,you have need of courage. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 24:10
        content: "  Or \u201Cyour strength is limited.\u201D Our weakness often becomes
          an excuse to quit, but strength and courage come as the result of faithfulness
          under pressure. Some interpret this to mean \u201CIf you fail to help others
          in their time of need, you will grow too weak to help yourself.\u201D    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Go and rescue the perishing! Be their savior!Why would you stand back
        and watch them stagger to their death?
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And why would you say, \u201CBut it\u2019s none of my business\u201D?The
        one who knows you completely and judges your every motiveis also the keeper
        of souls\u2014and not just yours!He sees through your excuses and holds you
        responsiblefor failing to help those whose lives are threatened."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Revelation-knowledge is a delicacy,sweet like flowing honey that melts
        in your mouth.Eat as much of it as you can, my friend!
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: For then you will perceive what is true wisdom,your future will be
        bright, [[COMMENT(0)]]and this hope living within you will never disappoint
        you.
      comments:
      - number: 24:14
        content: "  The Septuagint is \u201Cyour death will be good.\u201D    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Listen up, you wicked, irreverent ones\u2014don\u2019t harass the
        lovers of God [[COMMENT(0)]]and don\u2019t invade their resting place."
      comments:
      - number: 24:15
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe righteous.\u201D    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: For the lovers of God may suffer adversityand stumble seven times,but
        they will continue to rise over and over again.But the unrighteous are brought
        down by just one calamityand will never be able to rise again. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 24:16
        content: '  Implied in the text, as it completes the parallelism.    '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Never gloat when your enemy meets disaster,and don\u2019t be quick
        to rejoice if he falls."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: For the Lord, who sees your heart,will be displeased with you and
        will pity your foe.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Don\u2019t be angrily offended over evildoers or be agitated by them.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 24:19
        content: "  The Septuagint is \u201CDon\u2019t rejoice with those who do
          evil or be jealous of them.\u201D    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For the wicked have no life and no future\u2014their light of life
        will die out. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 24:20
        content: '  Not only will they die out, but the implication is they will
          also have no posterity.    '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "My child, stand in awe of <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>!Give counsel
        to others,but don\u2019t mingle with those who are rebellious."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Revelation from the Wise'
      title: Revelation from the Wise
      number: 22
      content: For sudden destruction will fall upon themand their lives will be
        ruined in a moment.And who knows what retribution they will face! [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 24:22
        content: '  Verses    and    are translated from the Aramaic.    '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Those enlightened with wisdom have spoken these proverbs:Judgment
        must be impartial,for it is always wrong to be swayed by a person\u2019s
        status."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "If you say to the guilty, \u201CYou are innocent,\u201Dthe nation
        will curse you and the people will revile you."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: But when you convict the guilty,the people will thank you and reward
        you with favor.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Speaking honestly is a sign of true friendship. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 24:26
        content: "  The Hebrew is literally \u201CAn honest answer is like a kiss
          on the lips.\u201D In the culture of the day, kissing was a sign of authentic
          friendship and a mark of relationship, which was often expressed in public
          among friends.    "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Go ahead, build your career and give yourself to your work.But if
        you put me first, you\u2019ll see your family built up! [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 24:27
        content: '  As translated from the Septuagint.  '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Why would you be a false accuser and slander with your words?
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Don\u2019t ever spitefully say, \u201CI\u2019ll get even with him!I\u2019ll
        do to him what he did to me!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30-31: '
      title: 
      number: 30-31
      content: One day I passed by the field of a lazy man,and I noticed the vineyards
        of a slacker.I observed nothing but thorns, weeds, and broken-down walls.
      comments: []
    - name: '30-31: '
      title: 
      number: 30-31
      content: One day I passed by the field of a lazy man,and I noticed the vineyards
        of a slacker.I observed nothing but thorns, weeds, and broken-down walls.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'So I considered their lack of wisdom,and I pondered the lessons I
        could learn from this:'
      comments: []
    - name: '33-34: '
      title: 
      number: 33-34
      content: Professional work habits prevent poverty from becomingyour permanent
        business partner. And:If you put off until tomorrow the work you could do
        today,tomorrow never seems to come.
      comments: []
    - name: '33-34: '
      title: 
      number: 33-34
      content: Professional work habits prevent poverty from becomingyour permanent
        business partner. And:If you put off until tomorrow the work you could do
        today,tomorrow never seems to come.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "Solomon\u2019s proverbs, published by the scribes of King Hezekiah:"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: God conceals the revelation of his word [[COMMENT(0)]]in the hiding
        place of his glory. But the honor of kings  is revealedby how they thoroughly
        search outthe deeper meaning of all that God says.
      comments:
      - number: 25:2
        content: "  Many translate this \u201Ca matter,\u201D whereas the Hebrew
          is  , which is translated more than eight hundred times in the Old Testament
          as \u201Cword.\u201D      There is beautiful poetry in the Hebrew text.
          The word for \u201Chide\u201D is  , and the word for \u201Cword\u201D is 
          . The Hebrew is actually \u201C  [glory]    [hidden]    [word].\u201D     
          We have been made kings and priests, royal lovers of God, because of God\u2019s
          grace and Christ\u2019s redeeming blood. See    and  .    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The heart of a king is full of understanding,like the heavens are
        high and the ocean is deep.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: If you burn away the impurities from silver,a sterling vessel will
        emerge from the fire.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And if you purge corruption from the kingdom,a king\u2019s reign
        will be established in righteousness."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Don\u2019t boast in the presence of a kingor promote yourself by
        taking a seat at the head tableand pretending that you\u2019re someone important."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "For it is better for the king to say to you,\u201CCome, you should
        sit at the head table,\u201Dthan for him to say in front of everyone,\u201CPlease
        get up and move\u2014you\u2019re sitting in the place of the prince.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Don\u2019t be hasty to file a lawsuit.By starting something you wish
        you hadn\u2019t,you could be humiliated when you lose your case."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Don\u2019t reveal another person\u2019s secretjust to prove a point
        in an argument,or you could be accused of being a gossip"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: and gain a reputation for being onewho betrays the confidence of a
        friend.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Winsome words spoken at just the right timeare as appealing as apples
        gilded in goldsurrounded with silver. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 25:11
        content: "  The Aramaic reads \u201CThe one who speaks the word is an apple
          of gold in a setting of silver.\u201D The Septuagint is \u201CA wise word
          is like a golden apple in a pendant of rubies.\u201D Each one of God\u2019s
          promises are like apples gilded in gold. When we are full of his Spirit,
          we can speak and prophesy words of encouragement that are spoken at the
          right time for the blessing of others.    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: When you humbly receive wise correction,it adorns your life with beauty
        [[COMMENT(0)]]and makes you a better person.
      comments:
      - number: 25:12
        content: "  Or \u201Can earring of gold, an ornament of fine gold.\u201D
          An earring pierces the ear and is an emblem of a listening heart.    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: A reliable, trustworthy messengerrefreshes the heart of his master,
        [[COMMENT(0)]]like a gentle snowfall at harvest time.
      comments:
      - number: 25:13
        content: "  Or \u201Cemployer.\u201D    "
    - name: '14: Wisdom Practices Self-Control'
      title: Wisdom Practices Self-Control
      number: 14
      content: "Clouds that carry no waterand a wind that brings no refreshing rain
        [[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014that\u2019s what you\u2019re like when you boastof a
        gift that you don\u2019t have. "
      comments:
      - number: 25:14
        content: "  The symbols of clouds, wind, and rain are significant. Clouds
          are often a metaphor for the people of God filled with glory (see  ;  ).
          Wind is an emblem of the Holy Spirit bringing new life (see  ). Rain often
          points to teaching the revelation-truths that refresh and water the seeds
          of spiritual growth (see  ). God\u2019s anointed people are to be clouds
          carried by the wind of the Holy Spirit that bring refreshing truths to
          his people. When we are empty and false, we are clouds without rain. See
          also    and  .      Or \u201Cboast of a promised gift you never intend
          to give.\u201D The Hebrew is literally \u201Cto make yourself shine in
          a gift of falsehood.\u201D    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Use patience and kindness when you want to persuade leadersand watch
        them change their minds right in front of you.For your gentle wisdom will
        quell the strongest resistance. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 25:15
        content: "  Or \u201CSoft words break bones.\u201D    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When you discover something sweet,don\u2019t overindulge and eat
        more than you need,for excess in anything can make you sick of even a good
        thing."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Don\u2019t wear out your welcomeby staying too long at the home of
        your friends,or they may get fed up with always having you thereand wish
        you hadn\u2019t come."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Lying about and slandering peopleare as bad as hitting them with a
        club,or wounding them with an arrow,or stabbing them with a sword.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "You can\u2019t depend on an unreliable personwhen you really need
        help.It can be compared to biting down on an abscessed toothor walking with
        a sprained ankle."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: When you sing a song of joy to someone sufferingin the deepest grief
        and heartache,it can be compared to disrobing in the middle of a blizzardor
        rubbing salt in a wound.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Is your enemy hungry? Buy him lunch. [[COMMENT(0)]]Win him over with
        your kindness.
      comments:
      - number: 25:21
        content: "  Or \u201CIs he thirsty? Give him a drink.\u201D    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Your surprising generosity will awaken his conscience [[COMMENT(0)]]and
        God will reward you with favor.
      comments:
      - number: 25:22
        content: "  Or \u201CYou will heap coals of fire on his head.\u201D His heart
          will be moved and his shame exposed.    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "As the north wind brings a storm,saying things you shouldn\u2019t
        [[COMMENT(0)]] brings a storm to any relationship."
      comments:
      - number: 25:23
        content: "  Or \u201Cwords of gossip.\u201D    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "It\u2019s better to live all alone in a rundown shackthan to share
        a castle with a crabby spouse! [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 25:24
        content: "  With the exception of one Hebrew letter, this verse is identical
          to  . See footnote. The Aramaic reads \u201Cthan to live with a contentious
          woman in a house of divisions.\u201D    "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Like a drink of cool water refreshes a weary, thirsty soul,so hearing
        good news revives the spirit.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: When a lover of God gives in and compromises with wickedness,it can
        be compared to contaminating a stream with sewageor polluting a fountain.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "It\u2019s good to eat sweet things,but you can take too much.It\u2019s
        good to be honored,but to seek words of praise [[COMMENT(0)]] is not honor
        at all."
      comments:
      - number: 25:27
        content: '  This line is translated from the Aramaic.  '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "If you live without restraintand are unable to control your temper,you\u2019re
        as helpless as a city with broken-down defenses,open to attack."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Don\u2019t Be a Fool"
      title: "Don\u2019t Be a Fool"
      number: 1
      content: "It is totally out of place to promote and honor a fool,just like
        it\u2019s out of place to have snow in the summerand rain at harvest time.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 26:1
        content: '  Both snow and rain are good in their proper season but harmful
          in the wrong season. So is it harmful to the fool if you promote and honor
          him prematurely.    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: An undeserved curse will be powerless to harm you.It may flutter over
        you like a bird,but it will find no place to land. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 26:2
        content: '  There is an implication in some Hebrew manuscripts that the curse
          will go back and land on the one who wrongly spoke it, like a bird going
          back to its nest.    '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Guide a horse with a whip,direct a donkey with a bridle,and lead a
        rebellious fool with a beating on his backside!
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Don\u2019t respond to the words of a fool with more foolish words,or
        you will become as foolish as he is!"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Instead, if you\u2019re asked a silly question,answer it with words
        of wisdom [[COMMENT(0)]]so the fool doesn\u2019t think he\u2019s so clever."
      comments:
      - number: 26:5
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic.    '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "If you choose a fool to represent you,you\u2019re asking for trouble.It
        will be as bad for you as cutting off your own feet!"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "You can never trust the words of a fool,just like a crippled man
        can\u2019t trust his legs to support him. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 26:7
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic.    '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Give honor to a fool and watch it backfire\u2014like a stone tied
        to a slingshot."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: The statements of a fool will hurt others [[COMMENT(0)]]like a thorn
        bush brandished by a drunk.
      comments:
      - number: 26:9
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic.    '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Like a reckless archer shooting arrows at randomis the impatient
        employerwho hires just any fool who comes along\u2014someone\u2019s going
        to get hurt! [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 26:10
        content: "  Implied in the context. This is a difficult verse to translate,
          and it reads quite differently in the Aramaic and the Septuagint. The Aramaic
          is \u201CA fool suffers much, like a drunkard crossing the sea.\u201D The
          Septuagint reads \u201CEvery fool endures much hardship and his fury comes
          to nothing.\u201D    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Fools are famous for repeating their errors,like dogs are known to
        return to their vomit.
      comments: []
    - name: "12: Don\u2019t Be Lazy"
      title: "Don\u2019t Be Lazy"
      number: 12
      content: "There\u2019s only one thing worse than a fool,and that\u2019s the
        smug, conceited manalways in love with his own opinions."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The lazy loafer says,\u201CI can\u2019t go out and look for a job\u2014there
        may be a lion out there roaming wild in the streets!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: As a door is hinged to the wall,so the lazy man keeps turning over,
        hinged to his bed!
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "There are some people so lazythey won\u2019t even work to feed themselves."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "A self-righteous person [[COMMENT(0)]] is convinced he\u2019s smarterthan
        seven wise counselors who tell him the truth."
      comments:
      - number: 26:16
        content: "  Or \u201Csluggard.\u201D This speaks of a person who lives in
          fantasy and not reality.    "
    - name: '17: Watch Your Words'
      title: Watch Your Words
      number: 17
      content: "It\u2019s better to grab a stray dog by its earsthan to meddle in
        a quarrel [[COMMENT(0)]]that\u2019s none of your business."
      comments:
      - number: 26:17
        content: "  Or \u201Cto become furious because of a quarrel that\u2019s not
          yours.\u201D    "
    - name: '18-19: '
      title: 
      number: 18-19
      content: "The one who is caught lying to his friend,who says, \u201CI didn\u2019t
        mean it, I was only joking,\u201Dcan be compared to a madmanrandomly shooting
        off deadly weapons."
      comments: []
    - name: '18-19: '
      title: 
      number: 18-19
      content: "The one who is caught lying to his friend,who says, \u201CI didn\u2019t
        mean it, I was only joking,\u201Dcan be compared to a madmanrandomly shooting
        off deadly weapons."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "It takes fuel to have a fire\u2014a fire dies down when you run out
        of fuel.So quarrels disappear when the gossip ends."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Add fuel to the fire and the blaze goes on.So add an argumentative
        man to the mix,and you\u2019ll keep strife alive."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Gossip is so delicious, and how we love to swallow it!For slander
        [[COMMENT(0)]] is easily absorbed into our innermost being.
      comments:
      - number: 26:22
        content: "  Or \u201Ccomplaining.\u201D    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Smooth talk [[COMMENT(0)]] can hide a corrupt heartjust like a pretty
        glaze covers a cheap clay pot.
      comments:
      - number: 26:23
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint. The Hebrew is \u201CBurning
          words.\u201D    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Kind words can be a cover to conceal hatred of others,for hypocrisy
        loves to hide behind flattery.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So don\u2019t be drawn in by the hypocrite,for his gracious speech
        is a charade,nothing but a masquerade covering his hatred and evil on parade.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 26:25
        content: "  The Hebrew is \u201Cseven abominations hide in his heart.\u201D
          This is a figure of speech for the fullness of evil, a heart filled to
          the brim with darkness.    "
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Don\u2019t worry\u2014he can\u2019t keep the mask on for long.One
        day his hypocrisy will be exposed before all the world."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Go ahead, set a trap for others\u2014and then watch as it snaps back
        on you!Start a landslide and you\u2019ll be the one who gets crushed."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Hatred is the root of slander [[COMMENT(0)]]and insecurity the root
        of flattery. '
      comments:
      - number: 26:28
        content: "  Or \u201CA slanderer hates his victims.\u201D      Or \u201CA
          flattering mouth works ruin.\u201D The Aramaic is \u201CMalicious words
          work trouble.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Heed Wisdom\u2019s Warnings"
      title: "Heed Wisdom\u2019s Warnings"
      number: 1
      content: "Never brag about the plans you have for tomorrow,for you don\u2019t
        have a clue what tomorrow may bring to you."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Let someone else honor you for your accomplishments,for self-praise
        is never appropriate.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "It\u2019s easier to carry a heavy boulder and a ton of sandthan to
        be provoked by a fool and have to carry that burden!"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The rage and anger of others can be overwhelming,but it\u2019s nothing
        compared to jealousy\u2019s fire."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "It\u2019s better to be corrected openlyif it stems from hidden love."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "You can trust a friend who wounds you with his honesty, [[COMMENT(0)]]but
        your enemy\u2019s pretended flattery  comes from insincerity."
      comments:
      - number: 27:6
        content: "  Or \u201CAmen [effective and faithful] are the wounds of love.\u201D
          This could be a reference to the wounds Jesus endured because of his love
          for us.      Or \u201Ckisses.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: When your soul is full, you turn down even the sweetest honey.But
        when your soul is starving,every bitter thing becomes sweet. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 27:7
        content: '  When we are full of many things and many opinions, the sweet
          word of God, like revelation honey, is spurned. Instead, we eat and fill
          our souls with things that can never satisfy.    '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Like a bird that has fallen from its nestis the one who is dislodged
        from his home. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 27:8
        content: "  Or \u201Cbanished from his place,\u201D as translated from the
          Aramaic.    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Sweet friendships [[COMMENT(0)]] refresh the soul and awaken our
        hearts with joy,for good friends are like the anointing oilthat yields the
        fragrant incense of God\u2019s presence. "
      comments:
      - number: 27:9
        content: "  Or \u201Ccounsel.\u201D      The Hebrew text refers to the sacred
          anointing oil and the incense that burns in the Holy Place.    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So never give up on a friend or abandon a friend of your father\u2014for
        in the day of your brokenness [[COMMENT(0)]]you won\u2019t have to run to
        a relative for help.A friend nearby is better than a relative far away."
      comments:
      - number: 27:10
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic.    '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "My son, when you walk in wisdom,my heart is filled with gladness,for
        the way you live is proofthat I\u2019ve not taught you in vain. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 27:11
        content: "  Or \u201Cthat I may answer those who reproach me.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "A wise, shrewd person discerns the danger aheadand prepares himself,but
        the na\xEFve simpleton never looks aheadand suffers the consequences."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Cosign for one you barely know and you will pay a great price!Anyone
        stupid enough to guarantee the loan of anotherdeserves to have his property
        seized in payment.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Do you think you\u2019re blessing your neighborswhen you sing at
        the top of your lungs early in the morning?Don\u2019t be fooled\u2014they\u2019ll
        curse you for doing it! [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 27:14
        content: "  Or \u201CHe who sings in a loud voice early in the morning, thinking
          he\u2019s blessing his neighbor, is no different from he who pronounces
          a curse.\u201D    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: An endless drip, drip, drip, from a leaky faucet [[COMMENT(0)]]and
        the words of a cranky, nagging wife have the same effect.
      comments:
      - number: 27:15
        content: "  Or \u201Ca constant drip on a rainy day.\u201D    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Can you stop the north wind from blowingor grasp a handful of oil?That\u2019s
        easier than to stop her from complaining."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: It takes a grinding wheel to sharpen a blade,and so one person sharpens
        the character of another.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Tend an orchard and you\u2019ll have fruit to eat.Serve the Master\u2019s
        interestsand you\u2019ll receive honor that\u2019s sweet."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Just as no two faces are exactly alike,so every heart is different.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 27:19
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic and the Septuagint.    '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Death and destruction are never filled,and the desires of men\u2019s
        hearts are insatiable."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Fire is the way to test the purity of silver and gold,but the character
        of a man is testedby giving him a measure of fame. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 27:21
        content: "  Or \u201Cby the things he praises.\u201D    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: You can beat a fool half to deathand still never beat the foolishness
        out of him. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 27:22
        content: "  Or \u201CIf you pound a fool in a mortar with a pestle like dried
          grain, still his foolishness will not depart from him.\u201D    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: A shepherd should pay close attention to the faces of his flockand
        hold close to his heart the condition of those he cares for.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "A man\u2019s strength, power, and riches [[COMMENT(0)]] will one
        day fade away;not even nations  endure forever."
      comments:
      - number: 27:24
        content: "  The Hebrew says merely \u201Criches,\u201D while the Aramaic
          adds \u201Cpower [dominion]\u201D and the Septuagint adds \u201Cstrength.\u201D
          This translation combines them.      Or \u201Ca crown\u201D or \u201Cdiadem
          [dominion].\u201D    "
    - name: '25-27: '
      title: 
      number: 25-27
      content: "Take care of your responsibilitiesand be diligent in your businessand
        you will have more than enough\u2014an abundance of food, clothing, and plenty
        for your household. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: "27:25\u201327"
        content: "  An agricultural analogy is used in the Hebrew and Aramaic. The
          analogy of a farming enterprise has been changed to business here in order
          to transfer meaning. It is literally \u201CGather the hay of the field
          and hills, and new grass will appear. Lambs will provide clothing, goats
          will pay for the price of the field, and there will be enough goat\u2019s
          milk for you, your family, and your servant girls.\u201D  "
    - name: '25-27: '
      title: 
      number: 25-27
      content: "Take care of your responsibilitiesand be diligent in your businessand
        you will have more than enough\u2014an abundance of food, clothing, and plenty
        for your household. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: "27:25\u201327"
        content: "  An agricultural analogy is used in the Hebrew and Aramaic. The
          analogy of a farming enterprise has been changed to business here in order
          to transfer meaning. It is literally \u201CGather the hay of the field
          and hills, and new grass will appear. Lambs will provide clothing, goats
          will pay for the price of the field, and there will be enough goat\u2019s
          milk for you, your family, and your servant girls.\u201D  "
    - name: '25-27: '
      title: 
      number: 25-27
      content: "Take care of your responsibilitiesand be diligent in your businessand
        you will have more than enough\u2014an abundance of food, clothing, and plenty
        for your household. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: "27:25\u201327"
        content: "  An agricultural analogy is used in the Hebrew and Aramaic. The
          analogy of a farming enterprise has been changed to business here in order
          to transfer meaning. It is literally \u201CGather the hay of the field
          and hills, and new grass will appear. Lambs will provide clothing, goats
          will pay for the price of the field, and there will be enough goat\u2019s
          milk for you, your family, and your servant girls.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Lovers of God'
      title: Lovers of God
      number: 1
      content: Guilty criminals experience paranoiaeven though no one threatens them.But
        the innocent lovers of God,because of righteousness,will have the boldness
        [[COMMENT(0)]] of a young, ferocious lion!
      comments:
      - number: 28:1
        content: "  Or \u201Cconfidence.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: A rebellious nation is thrown into chaos, [[COMMENT(0)]]but leaders
        anointed with wisdom will restore law and order.
      comments:
      - number: 28:2
        content: "  Or \u201CA rebellious nation will have one leader after another.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "When a pauper [[COMMENT(0)]] oppresses the destitute,it\u2019s like
        a flash flood that sweeps away their last hope."
      comments:
      - number: 28:3
        content: '  This pauper can also be one who is spiritually poor. Some Jewish
          expositors believe it refers to corrupt judges.    '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Those who turn their backs on what they know is right [[COMMENT(0)]]will
        no longer be able to tell right from wrong.But those who love the truth strengthen
        their souls. '
      comments:
      - number: 28:4
        content: "  The Hebrew word is \u201Cthe Torah.\u201D See vv.  ,  .     
          As translated from the Aramaic. The Septuagint is \u201Cbuild a wall to
          protect themselves.\u201D    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Justice never makes sense to men devoted to darkness,but those tenderly
        devoted to the Lordcan understand justice perfectly.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "It\u2019s more respectable to be poor and pure than rich and perverse."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "To be obedient to what you\u2019ve been taught [[COMMENT(0)]]proves
        you\u2019re an honorable child,but to socialize with the lawless brings shame
        to your parents."
      comments:
      - number: 28:7
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe Torah.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Go ahead and get rich on the backs of the poor,but all the wealth
        you gather will one day be givento those who are kind to the needy.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "If you close your heart and refuse to listen to God\u2019s instruction,
        [[COMMENT(0)]]even your prayer will be despised."
      comments:
      - number: 28:9
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe Torah.\u201D    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Those who tempt the lovers of God with an evil schemewill fall into
        their own traps.But the innocent who resist temptation will experience reward.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The wealthy in their conceit presume to be wise,but a poor person
        with discernment can see right through them.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The triumphant joy of God\u2019s lovers releases great glory. [[COMMENT(0)]]But
        when the wicked rise to power, everyone goes into hiding. "
      comments:
      - number: 28:12
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic.      Or \u201Cpeople become victims.\u201D    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "If you cover up your sin you\u2019ll never do well.But if you confess
        your sins and forsake them,you will be kissed by mercy."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Overjoyed is the one who with tender heart trembles before God,but
        the stubborn, unyielding heart will experience even greater evil.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Ruthless rulers can only be comparedto raging lions and roaming bears.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 28:15
        content: "  David, before he killed Goliath, went after the lion and the
          bear. See  . These beasts represented demonic forces of evil over the land.
          Daniel also mentions the world\u2019s ruthless leaders as lions and bears.
          See  .    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Abusive leaders fail to employ wisdom,but leaders who despise corruption
        [[COMMENT(0)]]will enjoy a long and full life. '
      comments:
      - number: 28:16
        content: "  Or \u201Cinjustice.\u201D      Or \u201Cenjoy a long reign.\u201D    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "A murderer\u2019s conscience will torment him\u2014a fugitive haunted
        by guilt all the way to the gravewith no one to support him."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: The pure will be rescued from failure,but the perverse will suddenly
        fall into ruin.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Work hard and you\u2019ll have all you desire,but chase a fantasy
        [[COMMENT(0)]] and you could end up with nothing."
      comments:
      - number: 28:19
        content: "  Or \u201Can empty dream.\u201D The Septuagint is \u201Cthe one
          who pursues leisure.\u201D    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Life\u2019s blessings drench the honest and faithful person,but punishment
        rains down upon the greedy and dishonest."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Giving favoritism to the rich and powerful is disgusting,and this
        is done by the type of judge who would betray a man for a bribe. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 28:21
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic.    '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "A greedy man [[COMMENT(0)]] is in a race to get rich,but he forgets
        that he could lose what\u2019s most importantand end up with nothing. "
      comments:
      - number: 28:22
        content: "  Both the Aramaic and Hebrew have \u201CThe man with an evil eye.\u201D
          This is a figure of speech for a stingy or greedy man. A person who shuts
          his heart to the poor is said to have an evil eye. A person with a good
          eye is someone who looks on the poor with generosity.      As translated
          from the Aramaic. The Aramaic text sounds very similar to what Jesus says
          about gaining the world but losing our souls. See  .    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: If you correct someone with constructive criticism,in the end he will
        appreciate it more than flattery.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "A person who would reject his own parents [[COMMENT(0)]] and say,\u201CWhat\u2019s
        wrong with that?\u201D is as bad as a murderer."
      comments:
      - number: 28:24
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint. The Hebrew is \u201Cthe one
          who steals from his own parents.\u201D    "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: To make rash, hasty decisionsshows that you are not trusting the Lord.But
        when you rely totally on God,you will still act carefully and prudently.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 28:25
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint. The Hebrew is \u201CThe greedy
          person stirs up trouble, but the one who trusts in the Lord will prosper.\u201D    "
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Self-confident know-it-alls [[COMMENT(0)]] will prove to be fools.But
        when you lean on the wisdom from above,you will have a way to escape the
        troubles of your own making.
      comments:
      - number: 28:26
        content: "  Or \u201Cthose who trust their instincts.\u201D    "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "You will never go without if you give to the poor.But if you\u2019re
        heartless, stingy, and selfish, [[COMMENT(0)]]you invite curses upon yourself."
      comments:
      - number: 28:27
        content: "  Or \u201Cif you hide your eyes from the poor.\u201D  "
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: When wicked leaders rise to power,good people go into hiding.But when
        they fall from power,the godly take their place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Don\u2019t Be Stubborn"
      title: "Don\u2019t Be Stubborn"
      number: 1
      content: Stubborn people who repeatedly refuse to accept correctionwill suddenly
        be broken and never recover.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Everyone rejoices when the lovers of God flourish,but the people groan
        when the wicked rise to power.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: When you love wisdom, your father is overjoyed.But when you associate
        with prostitutes,you waste your wealth in exchange for disgrace. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 29:3
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: A godly leader who values justiceis a great strength and example to
        the people.But the one who sells his influence for moneytears down what is
        right. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 29:4
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Flattery can often be used as a trap to hide ulterior motivesand take
        advantage of you.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: The wicked always have a trap laid for others,but the lovers of God
        escape as they sing and shoutin joyous triumph!
      comments: []
    - name: "7: You Can\u2019t Argue with a Fool"
      title: "You Can\u2019t Argue with a Fool"
      number: 7
      content: "God\u2019s righteous people will pour themselves out for the poor,
        [[COMMENT(0)]]but the ungodly make no attempt to understand or help the needy."
      comments:
      - number: 29:7
        content: '  The Hebrew text implies standing up for the legal rights of the
          poor.    '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Arrogant cynics love to pick fights,but the humble and wise love to
        pursue peace.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "There\u2019s no use arguing with a fool, [[COMMENT(0)]]for his ranting
        and raving prevent you from making a caseand settling the argument in a calm
        way."
      comments:
      - number: 29:9
        content: '  The Hebrew implies an argument in a court of law.    '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Violent men hate those with integrity,but the lovers of God esteem
        those who are holy. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 29:10
        content: '  As translated from the Septuagint.    '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: You can recognize fools by the waythey give full vent to their rageand
        let their words fly!But the wise bite their tongues and hold back all they
        could say.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: When leaders listen to false accusations,their associates become scoundrels.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Poor people and their oppressorshave only one thing in common\u2014God
        made them both. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 29:13
        content: "  A figure of speech in Hebrew that can literally be translated
          \u201CGod gave them both the gift of eyesight.\u201D The Septuagint is
          \u201CThe contracts between lenders and debtors are observed by the Lord.\u201D    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The best insurance for a leader\u2019s longevityis to demonstrate
        justice for the poor."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Experiencing many corrections and rebukes will make you wise.But
        if left to your own ways, you\u2019ll bring disgrace to your parents. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 29:15
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint. The Hebrew is \u201Cyour mother.\u201D    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: When the wicked are in power, lawlessness abounds.But the patient
        lovers of God will one day watch in triumphas their stronghold topples!
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Correct your child and one day you\u2019ll find he has changedand
        will bring you great delight."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "When there is no clear prophetic vision, [[COMMENT(0)]]people quickly
        wander astray. But when you follow the revelation of the Word,heaven\u2019s
        bliss fills your soul."
      comments:
      - number: 29:18
        content: "  The Hebrew word used here can refer to a \u201Cvision of the
          night,\u201D \u201Cdream,\u201D \u201Coracle,\u201D or \u201Crevelation.\u201D
          The Septuagint reads \u201Cwhere there is no prophetic seer [or interpreter].\u201D     
          Or \u201Clet loose,\u201D \u201Cstrip,\u201D or \u201Cmade themselves naked.\u201D
          The Septuagint reads \u201Cthe people become lawless.\u201D    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "A stubborn servant can\u2019t be corrected by words alone.For even
        if he understands, he pays no attention to you."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "There\u2019s only one kind of person who is worse than a fool:the
        impetuous one who speaks without thinking first."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "If you pamper your servants,don\u2019t be surprised when they expect
        to be treated as sons. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 29:21
        content: "  Or \u201CIf you pamper your servant when he is young, he\u2019ll
          become a weakling in the end.\u201D The Septuagint reads \u201CIf you live
          in luxury as a child, you\u2019ll become a domestic [servant] and at last
          will be grieved with yourself.\u201D The Aramaic states, \u201CYou\u2019ll
          be uprooted in the end.\u201D    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: The source of strife is found in an angry heart,for sin surrounds
        the life of a furious man. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 29:22
        content: "  The Hebrew word translated as \u201Ca furious man\u201D can also
          mean \u201Clord of fury\u201D or \u201CBaal of wrath.\u201D    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Lift yourself up with pride and you will soon be brought low, [[COMMENT(0)]]but
        a meek and humble spirit will add to your honor.
      comments:
      - number: 29:23
        content: "  Or \u201Cto depression.\u201D    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: You are your own worst enemy when you partner with a thief,for a curse
        of guilt will come upon youwhen you fail to report a crime. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 29:24
        content: "  Or \u201Cwhen under oath to testify but you do not talk.\u201D  "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Fear and intimidation is a trap that holds you back.But when you place
        your confidence in the Lord,you will be seated in the high place.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Everyone curries favor with leaders.But God is the judge, and justice
        comes from him.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "The wicked hate those who live a godly life,but the righteous hate
        injustice wherever it\u2019s found."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Mysterious Sayings of Agur'
      title: The Mysterious Sayings of Agur
      number: 1
      content: "These are the collected sayings of the prophet Agur, Jakeh\u2019s
        son [[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014the amazing revelation  he imparted to Ithiel and
        Ukal. "
      comments:
      - number: 30:1
        content: "  This section of Proverbs is attributed to Agur, who gave these
          oracles to his prot\xE9g\xE9s Ithiel and Ukal. Agur means \u201Cto gather
          a harvest.\u201D He was the son of Jakeh, which means \u201Cblameless\u201D
          or \u201Cobedient.\u201D Jakeh could be another name for David, Solomon\u2019s
          father. Many Jewish expositors believe that Agur was a pseudonym for Solomon.
          Nothing more is mentioned about Agur in the Bible than what we have here,
          which is typical for other prophets mentioned in the Scriptures. Some believe
          he could be the \u201Cmaster of the collection of sayings\u201D referred
          to in  .      Or \u201Cmighty prophecy.\u201D      The name Ithiel can
          mean \u201CGod is with me\u201D or \u201CGod has arrived.\u201D This was
          fulfilled by Christ, for his birth was the advent, the arrival of God to
          the earth in human form. Ukal means \u201CI am able\u201D or \u201CI am
          strong and mighty.\u201D When placed together, the meaning of these Hebrew
          names could read \u201CGather a harvest of sons who are blameless and obedient.
          They will have God with them, and they will be strong and mighty.\u201D
          This chapter contains some of the most mystical and mysterious sayings
          found in Proverbs, with hints of revelation from the book of Job.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "God, I\u2019m so weary and worn out,I feel more like a beast than
        a man.I was made in your image, [[COMMENT(0)]]but I lack understanding."
      comments:
      - number: 30:2
        content: '  Implied in the text, which is extraordinarily difficult to translate
          with certainty.    '
    - name: '3: Six Questions'
      title: Six Questions
      number: 3
      content: "I\u2019ve yet to learn the wisdomthat comes from the full and intimate
        knowledge of you,the Holy One."
      comments: []
    - name: "4: A Pure Heart Is Filled with God\u2019s Word"
      title: "A Pure Heart Is Filled with God\u2019s Word"
      number: 4
      content: Who is it that travels back and forthfrom the heavenly realm to the
        earth? [[COMMENT(0)]]Who controls the wind  as it blows and holds it in his
        fists?Who tucks the rain into the cloak of his clouds?Who stretches out the
        skyline from one vista to the other?What is his name?And what is the name
        of his Son?Who can tell me?
      comments:
      - number: 30:4
        content: '  Jesus solves this riddle in  . Only Jesus Christ is the master
          of heavenly knowledge and wisdom. See also  .      The Hebrew word    (wind)
          is also the term used for the Holy Spirit.    '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Every promise from the faithful Godis pure and proves to be true.He
        is a wraparound shield of protection for all his loverswho run to hide in
        him.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Never add to his words,or he will have to rebuke you and prove that
        you\u2019re a liar."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "God, there are two things I\u2019m asking you for before I die, only
        two:"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Empty out of my heart everything that is false\u2014every lie, and
        every crooked thing.And give me neither undue poverty nor undue wealth\u2014but
        rather, feed my soul with the measure of prosperitythat pleases you."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "May my satisfaction be found in you.Don\u2019t let me be so rich
        that I don\u2019t need youor so poor that I have to resort to dishonestyjust
        to make ends meet.Then my life will never detract from bringing glory to
        your name."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Never defame a servant before his master,for you will be the guilty
        oneand a curse will come upon you.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: There is a generation rising that curses their fathersand speaks evil
        of their mothers.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: There is a generation rising that considers themselvesto be pure in
        their own eyes, [[COMMENT(0)]]yet they are morally filthy,  unwashed, and
        unclean.
      comments:
      - number: 30:12
        content: '  See  .      The Hebrew uses the word  .    '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: There is a generation rising that is so filled with pride,they think
        they are superior and look down on others.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: There is a generation rising that uses their words like swordsto cut
        and slash those who are different.They would devour the poor, the needy,
        and the afflictedfrom off the face of the earth!
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "There are three words to describe the greedy:\u201CGive me more!\u201DThere
        are some things that are never satisfied.Forever craving more, they\u2019re
        unable to say, \u201CThat\u2019s enough!\u201DHere are four:"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "the grave, yawning for another victim,the barren womb, ever wanting
        a child,thirsty soil, ever longing for rain,and a raging fire, devouring
        its fuel.They\u2019re all insatiable."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Four Mysteries'
      title: Four Mysteries
      number: 17
      content: 'The eye that mocks his father and dishonors his elderly mother [[COMMENT(0)]]deserves
        to be plucked out by the ravens of the valleyand fed to the young vultures! '
      comments:
      - number: 30:17
        content: '  As translated from the Septuagint.      This is a figure of speech
          for demonic powers that will remove their vision. Ravens and vultures are
          unclean birds associated with demonic powers in Hebrew poetry.    '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "There are four marvelous mysteriesthat are too amazing to unravel
        [[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014who could fully explain them? "
      comments:
      - number: 30:18
        content: '  The Hebrew uses a poetic style of saying there are three mysteries,
          then saying there are four in order to emphasize their great importance.
          There could be within this poetic device a pointing to the fourth as the
          key, or the most important.      Notice that each of these four examples
          have to do with movement and mystery.    '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The way an eagle flies in the sky, [[COMMENT(0)]]the way a snake
        glides on a boulder, the path of a ship as it passes through the sea, and
        the way a bridegroom falls in love with his bride. '
      comments:
      - number: 30:19
        content: "  This is a picture of the overcoming life that soars above its
          problems and limitations with the wings of an eagle. It could also be a
          hint of the prophetic revelation that comes to God\u2019s servants mysteriously
          and supernaturally. See    and  .      The snake becomes a picture of our
          sin that was placed on the Rock, Jesus Christ. See  ;  ;  .      This is
          a picture of the way our lives, like a ship, sail on the high seas of mystery
          until we reach our destiny. Our lives contain mysteries, such as where
          God decided that we were to be born, how we were raised, and the companions
          who join us until we reach our desired haven. See  .      The Hebrew word
          translated \u201Cbride\u201D can also mean \u201Cvirgin,\u201D pointing
          to a wedding, thus implying the use of \u201Cbridegroom\u201D instead of
          \u201Cman.\u201D (Consider Ruth and Boaz.) More important, this is a beautiful
          metaphor for the mystery of the love of our heavenly Bridegroom (Jesus),
          who romances his bride and sweeps us off our feet. Love is a mystery. See
          also    and  .    "
    - name: '20: Four Intolerable Things'
      title: Four Intolerable Things
      number: 20
      content: "Here is the deceptive way of the adulterous woman: [[COMMENT(0)]]she
        takes what she wants and then says,\u201CI\u2019ve done nothing wrong.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 30:20
        content: '  The adulterous woman of Proverbs is a metaphor for the corrupt
          religious system. See  .    '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'There are four intolerable eventsthat [[COMMENT(0)]] are simply unbearable
        to observe:'
      comments:
      - number: 30:21
        content: "  See the first footnote for v.  . These four events each depict
          a promotion undeserved, a displacing of one who is virtuous with one who
          is corrupt. Each promotion indicates that they will carry their corruption
          with them. The unfaithful servant will likely become a tyrant. The fool
          who becomes wealthy will squander his wealth. The unfaithful woman (or
          \u201Chated woman\u201D) will continue her immorality even after she\u2019s
          married. The girlfriend who replaced the faithful wife will likely find
          another man one day.    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: when an unfaithful servant becomes a ruler,when a scoundrel comes
        into great wealth,
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Four Creatures Small and Wise'
      title: Four Creatures Small and Wise
      number: 23
      content: when an unfaithful woman marries a good man,and when a mistress replaces
        a faithful wife.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The earth has four creatures that are very small but very wise: [[COMMENT(0)]]'
      comments:
      - number: 30:24
        content: "  Or \u201CThey are the epitome of wisdom.\u201D    "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: The feeble ant has little strength,yet look how it diligently gathers
        its food in the summerto last throughout the winter. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 30:25
        content: '  To prepare for the future is a mark of true wisdom.    '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "The delicate rock-badger isn\u2019t all that strong,yet look how
        it makes a secure home, nestled in the rocks. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 30:26
        content: '  This becomes a picture of the believer. Though feeling weakness
          at times, we can make our home in the high place, inside the cleft of the
          Rock. See  .    '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: The locusts have no king to lead them,yet they cooperate as they move
        forward by bands. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 30:27
        content: '  The locust army points us to  . There is an awakening army coming
          to devour the works of the enemy. Their King, though invisible, guides
          them from on high as one army.    '
    - name: '28: Four Stately Things'
      title: Four Stately Things
      number: 28
      content: "And the small lizard [[COMMENT(0)]] is easy to catchas it clings
        to the walls with its hands,yet it can be found inside a king\u2019s palace. "
      comments:
      - number: 30:28
        content: "  Or \u201Cspider.\u201D      Though we may see ourselves as insignificant
          (like the small lizard), God can place us in significant places where we
          can be used for him.    "
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'There are four stately monarchs [[COMMENT(0)]]who are impressive
        to watch as they go forth:'
      comments:
      - number: 30:29
        content: '  See the first footnote on v.  .    '
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: the lion, the king of the jungle, who is afraid of no one,
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'the rooster strutting boldly among the hens, [[COMMENT(0)]]the male
        goat out in front leading the herd,and a king leading his regal procession. '
      comments:
      - number: 30:31
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint.      Or \u201Ca king surrounded
          by his band of soldiers.\u201D The Hebrew text is abstruse.    "
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "If you\u2019ve acted foolishly by drawing attention to yourself,or
        if you\u2019ve thought about saying something stupid,you\u2019d better shut
        your mouth."
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: For such stupidity may give you a bloody nose!Stirring up an argument
        only leads to an angry confrontation. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 30:33
        content: "  Or \u201CChurning milk makes butter, and punching the nose brings
          blood, so stirring up anger produces quarrels.\u201D The Hebrew contains
          a word play with the word  , which is almost identical to the word for
          \u201Cnose.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Inspired Word'
      title: Inspired Word
      number: 1
      content: "King Lemuel\u2019s [[COMMENT(0)]] royal words of wisdom:These are
        the inspired words my mother taught me. "
      comments:
      - number: 31:1
        content: "  Jewish legend is that King Lemuel was a pseudonym for Solomon,
          which would make his mother mentioned here to be Bathsheba. There is no
          other mention of Lemuel in the Scriptures. The Hebrew word translated \u201Cinspired
          words\u201D is  , which some have surmised was a place, meaning \u201CLemuel,
          King of Massa.\u201D      The Septuagint is \u201CThese are words spoken
          by God, and through a king came an answer divine.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Listen, my dear son, son of my womb.You are the answer to my prayers,
        my son.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So keep yourself sexually purefrom the promiscuous, wayward woman.Don\u2019t
        waste the strength of your anointingon those who ruin kings\u2014you\u2019ll
        live to regret it! [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 31:3
        content: '  As translated from the Septuagint.    '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For you are a king, Lemuel,and it\u2019s never fitting for a king
        to be drunk on wineor for rulers to crave alcohol."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: For when they drink they forget justiceand ignore the rights of those
        in need,those who depend on them for leadership.
      comments: []
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: Strong drink is given to the terminally ill,who are suffering at the
        brink of death.Wine is for those in depressionin order to drown their sorrows.Let
        them drink and forget their poverty and misery.
      comments: []
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: Strong drink is given to the terminally ill,who are suffering at the
        brink of death.Wine is for those in depressionin order to drown their sorrows.Let
        them drink and forget their poverty and misery.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: But you are to be a king who speaks up on behalfof the disenfranchisedand
        pleads for the legal rights of the defenselessand those who are dying.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Radiant Bride'
      title: The Radiant Bride
      number: 9
      content: Be a righteous king, judging on behalf of the poorand interceding
        for those most in need. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 31:9
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Who could ever find a wife like this one [[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014she
        is a woman of strength and mighty valor! She\u2019s full of wealth and wisdom.The
        price paid for her was greater  than many jewels."
      comments:
      - number: 31:10
        content: "  Starting with verse    through the end of the book, we have a
          Hebrew acrostic poem. It is alphabetical in structure, with each of the
          twenty-two verses beginning with a consecutive letter of the Hebrew alphabet.
          The implication is that the perfections of this woman would exhaust the
          entire language. The subject is the perfect bride, the virtuous woman.
          This woman is both a picture of a virtuous wife and an incredible allegory
          of the end-time victorious bride of Jesus Christ, full of virtue and grace.     
          The Hebrew word used to describe this virtuous wife is  . The meaning of
          this word cannot be contained by one English equivalent word. It is often
          used in connection with military prowess. This is a warring wife.    can
          be translated \u201Cmighty;\u201D \u201Cwealthy;\u201D \u201Cexcellent;\u201D
          \u201Cmorally righteous;\u201D \u201Cfull of substance, integrity, abilities,
          and strength;\u201D \u201Cmighty like an army.\u201D The wife is a metaphor
          for the last-days church, the virtuous, overcoming bride of Jesus Christ.
          The word    is most often used to describe valiant men. See  , where it
          is used for the mighty ones Moses was to commission as elders and leaders
          among the people. Because many of the cultural terms and metaphors used
          in this passage are not understood or even used in today\u2019s English-speaking
          world, this translation makes them explicit.      Or \u201Cher worth.\u201D
          The price paid for her was the sacred blood of the Lamb of God, her Bridegroom.    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Her husband has entrusted his heart to her, [[COMMENT(0)]]for she
        brings him the rich spoils of victory.
      comments:
      - number: 31:11
        content: "  Or \u201Chas great confidence in her.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: All throughout her life she brings him what is good and not evil.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 31:12
        content: '  The virtuous bride will not bring disgrace to his name. Jesus
          will not be ashamed to display her to the world.    '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'She searches out continually to possessthat which is pure and righteous.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]She delights in the work of her hands. '
      comments:
      - number: 31:13
        content: "  Or \u201Cwool and linen [flax].\u201D Wool is a metaphor often
          used as a symbol of what is pure. See  ;  ;  . Linen was made from flax
          and always speaks of righteousness. The priests of the Old Testament wore
          linen garments as they went before God\u2019s presence to offer sacrifices.
          The curtains of the tabernacle were likewise made of linen, signifying
          God\u2019s righteousness. See    and  . The virtuous bride of Christ in
          the last days will be seeking for only what is pure and righteous in the
          eyes of her Bridegroom.      Or \u201Ceagerly works with her hands.\u201D
          The hands, with their five fingers, speak of the five ministries of the
          present work of Christ on the earth: apostles, prophets, evangelists, pastors,
          and teachers. These are often referred to as the five-fold ministries.
          Her delight is to equip others and help those in need.    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'She gives out revelation-truth [[COMMENT(0)]] to feed others.She
        is like a trading ship bringing divine supplies from the merchant. '
      comments:
      - number: 31:14
        content: "  Or \u201Cbread.\u201D This is a consistent emblem of spiritual
          food.      Or \u201Csupplies from far away.\u201D The implication is that
          the supplies come from another realm. She is bringing heavenly manna for
          those she feeds.      Or \u201Clike merchant ships bringing goods.\u201D
          Like a ship loaded with cargo, the bride of Christ brings heavenly treasures
          to others. The use of the term    points to Jesus Christ. He is described
          as a merchant in    in the parable of the extraordinary pearl. The \u201Cpearl\u201D
          is the church or the believer, which cost all that Jesus had (his blood)
          to purchase us.    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Even in the night season [[COMMENT(0)]] she arises  and sets food
        on the tablefor hungry ones in her house and for others. '
      comments:
      - number: 31:15
        content: "  She is interceding in the night, laboring in a night season to
          help others.      The Hebrew word translated \u201Carise\u201D can also
          mean \u201Cto rise up in power.\u201D We are told to \u201Crise up in splendor
          and be radiant, for your light has dawned\u201D in  , which uses the same
          Hebrew word for \u201Carise.\u201D The bride of Christ will arise with
          anointing to feed and bless the people of God.      Or \u201Cfemale servants.\u201D
          The servants are a metaphor for other churches and ministries.    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'She sets her heart upon a field [[COMMENT(0)]] and takes it as her
        own.She labors there to plant the living vines. '
      comments:
      - number: 31:16
        content: "  Or \u201Ca land\u201D or \u201Ca country.\u201D      Or \u201CBy
          the fruit of her hands she plants a vineyard.\u201D (The Septuagint is
          \u201Cpossession.\u201D) For \u201Chands,\u201D see the second footnote
          for v.  . This vineyard becomes a metaphor for the local church. We are
          the branches of the Vine (Christ). See  . She is passionate about bringing
          forth fruit. She becomes a missionary to the nations, planting churches
          and bringing new life.    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: She wraps herself in strength, [[COMMENT(0)]] might, and power in
        all her works.
      comments:
      - number: 31:17
        content: "  Or \u201CShe girds her loins with strength and makes her shoulders
          strong.\u201D This is a figure of speech for being anointed with power
          to do the works of Jesus. See  .    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'She tastes and experiences a better substance, [[COMMENT(0)]]and
        her shining light will not be extinguished,no matter how dark the night. '
      comments:
      - number: 31:18
        content: "  Or \u201Cgood merchandise.\u201D      Her prayer life (\u201Clight\u201D)
          overcomes her circumstances, even in a culture where darkness prevails.    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'She stretches out her hands to help the needy [[COMMENT(0)]]and she
        lays hold of the wheels of government. '
      comments:
      - number: 31:19
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint. The Hebrew uses a term for
          \u201Cdistaff\u201D (a weaver\u2019s staff), which is taken from a root
          word for \u201Cprosperity.\u201D The poetic nuance of this phrase is that
          she uses her prosperity to bless the needy.      Or \u201CHer hands grasp
          the spindle.\u201D The word translated as \u201Cspindle\u201D can also
          mean \u201Cgovernmental circuits\u201D or \u201Cwheels.\u201D There is
          a hint here of the wheels mentioned in  . The throne of God\u2019s government
          sits on flaming wheels. See  .    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: She is known by her extravagant generosity to the poor,for she always
        reaches out her hands [[COMMENT(0)]] to those in need.
      comments:
      - number: 31:20
        content: '  Notice the mention of her hands. See the second footnote for
          v.  .    '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: She is not afraid of tribulation, [[COMMENT(0)]]for all her household
        is covered in the dual garments of righteousness and grace.
      comments:
      - number: 31:21
        content: "  Or \u201Csnow.\u201D This is a figure of speech for the fear
          of a cold winter season.      As translated from the Septuagint. The Hebrew
          is \u201Ceveryone is covered in scarlet [blood].\u201D Grace has brought
          righteousness to those in her house (under her ministry).    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Her clothing is beautifully knit together [[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014a purple
        gown of exquisite linen."
      comments:
      - number: 31:22
        content: '  This clothing speaks of the ministries of the body of Christ,
          woven and knit together by the Holy Spirit. See    and  .    '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Her husband is famous and admired by all,sitting as the venerable
        judge of his people. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 31:23
        content: "  Or \u201Csitting at the city gates among the elders of the land.\u201D
          Judgment was rendered at the gates of a city in that day. It was their
          courtroom. Our heavenly King is also the Judge. So famous, so glorious,
          yet he is our Bridegroom.    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Even her works of righteousness [[COMMENT(0)]]she does  for the benefit
        of her enemies. '
      comments:
      - number: 31:24
        content: "  Or \u201Clinen.\u201D See the second footnote for v.    regarding
          linen as a symbol for righteousness.      Or \u201Csells them.\u201D The
          root word for \u201Csell\u201D can also mean \u201Csurrender.\u201D     
          Or \u201Caprons or belts for the Canaanites.\u201D The Canaanites were
          the traditional enemies of the Hebrews.    "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Bold power and glorious majesty [[COMMENT(0)]] are wrapped around
        heras she laughs with joy over the latter days. '
      comments:
      - number: 31:25
        content: "  Or \u201CBeauty, honor, and excellence.\u201D      The virtuous
          and victorious bride has no fear for the days to come. She contemplates
          eternity and her forever union with the Bridegroom.    "
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Her teachings are filled with wisdom and kindnessas loving instruction
        pours from her lips. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 31:26
        content: "  The Septuagint is \u201Cshe opens her mouth carefully and lawfully.\u201D    "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: She watches over the ways of her household [[COMMENT(0)]]and meets
        every need they have.
      comments:
      - number: 31:27
        content: "  Or \u201CShe is a watchman over her house [family].\u201D    "
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Her sons and daughters arise [[COMMENT(0)]] in one accord to extol
        her virtues, and her husband arises to speak of her in glowing terms. '
      comments:
      - number: 31:28
        content: "  The Hebrew word translated \u201Carise\u201D can also mean \u201Cto
          rise up with power.\u201D The Septuagint is \u201CShe raises her children
          so they will grow rich.\u201D      Or \u201CHooray, hooray for our mother!\u201D     
          For more of how the heavenly Bridegroom loves his bride, read the Song
          of Songs.    "
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CThere are many valiant and noble ones, [[COMMENT(0)]]but you
        have ascended above them all!\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: 31:29
        content: "  Or \u201CMany daughters have obtained wealth because of her.\u201D
          These valiant and noble ones (daughters) represent the church of previous
          generations who remained faithful in their pursuit of Jesus. But this final
          generation will be the bridal company of the lovers of God who do mighty
          exploits and miracles on the earth.      Or \u201Cyou are first in his
          eyes.\u201D See  .    "
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Charm can be misleading,and beauty is vain and so quickly fades,but
        this virtuous woman lives in the wonder, awe,and fear of the Lord.She will
        be praised throughout eternity.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: So go ahead and give her the credit that is due,for she has become
        a radiant woman,and all her loving works of righteousness deserve to be admiredat
        the gateways of every city! [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 31:31
        content: "  The Septuagint could be translated \u201Cher husband is praised
          at the city gates.\u201D  "
